01:28.388 --> 01:32.091
♪ [ Melodramatic ]

01:42.635 --> 01:46.238
♪ [ Upbeat ]

02:02.455 --> 02:06.391
♪ [ Lively ]

02:14.567 --> 02:18.770
<i>♪ [ "Battle Hymn</i>
<i>      Of The Republic" ]</i>

02:30.517 --> 02:34.920
<i>♪ [ Dramatic ]</i>

03:15.862 --> 03:19.565
[ Chattering, Laughter ]

03:25.939 --> 03:30.409
[ Bell Ringing ]
[ Man ]
My friends--

03:32.345 --> 03:36.248
Ready for dessert?
[ All ]
Yeah!

03:36.482 --> 03:39.518
Specialty of the house
is served chilled,

03:39.520 --> 03:42.754
but it melts very quickly.
[ All Laugh ]

03:42.756 --> 03:46.959
So I suggest
that we gobble it up.

03:48.595 --> 03:52.998
[ All Exclaim, Applaud ]

04:23.429 --> 04:28.634
<i>Yes?</i>
<i>Yeah, I'd like to see</i>
<i>Stanford White.</i>

04:28.636 --> 04:31.503
<i>Who, may I ask,</i>
<i>is calling?</i>

04:31.505 --> 04:34.906
Uh, here's my card.

04:39.779 --> 04:42.047
[ Gasps ]

04:56.296 --> 04:58.497
Sir--

05:00.767 --> 05:03.735
Are you in there, White?

05:03.737 --> 05:06.972
[ Pounding Continues ]

05:06.974 --> 05:09.308
Open the door!

05:09.310 --> 05:12.911
- [ Shouting ] White!
- <i>♪ [ Stops ]</i>

05:14.080 --> 05:16.548
Who is it?

05:17.450 --> 05:22.487
You know who it is.
You know damn well who it is!

05:23.723 --> 05:28.060
- Harry K. Thaw of Pittsburgh!
- [ Guests Murmur ]

05:28.428 --> 05:31.830
Don't you think this is
a bit irregular, Mr. Thaw?

05:31.832 --> 05:33.699
Look, I want to talk to you!

05:33.701 --> 05:35.500
Hardly a way to go about it,
Mr. Thaw.

05:35.502 --> 05:40.605
- [ Gasping ]
- Don't play with me, White!
Look, open the door,

05:40.607 --> 05:43.508
or some friends of mine
will open it for me.

05:43.510 --> 05:45.711
<i>I'm serious!</i>

05:45.713 --> 05:47.679
What-What do you want?

05:47.681 --> 05:51.550
[ Scoffs ]
White, I'm here for the statue.

05:51.552 --> 05:57.422
I'm takin' it down!
I'm getting tired
of this ridiculous business.

05:57.424 --> 05:59.991
Why don't you go away now...

05:59.993 --> 06:03.695
and save me the trouble
of calling the police?

06:06.766 --> 06:10.035
- [ Crashing ]
- [ Gasping ]

06:14.040 --> 06:18.477
- <i>[ Door Breaks ]</i>
<i>-[ All Gasp ]</i>

06:20.747 --> 06:24.750
<i>Goddamn it, Thaw,</i>
<i>that door is priceless!</i>

06:24.752 --> 06:26.885
<i>When are you going to stop</i>
<i>this ridiculous charade?</i>

06:26.887 --> 06:30.055
You're the one
that's creating the scandal!
I can see what's goin' on here.

06:30.057 --> 06:33.492
- Mr. Thaw--
- I know what you do
with your chorus girls.

06:33.494 --> 06:36.995
- Mr. Thaw--
- I know what
all you people are up to!

06:36.997 --> 06:38.830
I'm sure the police'd
like to know too.

06:38.832 --> 06:43.168
Mr. Thaw, let me introduce
Commissioner of Police
Rheinlander Waldo.

06:43.170 --> 06:49.574
I'm sure he'll be fascinated
by all the stories
you have to tell.

06:49.576 --> 06:52.411
Look, I'm not a fool.

06:52.413 --> 06:54.413
You hear me?
I'm not a fool.

06:54.415 --> 06:57.149
I know exactly
what I'm doing.

06:57.151 --> 07:02.654
'Cause I'm smart.
I'm smarter than you are.

07:05.658 --> 07:08.059
[ Guests Murmuring ]

07:11.097 --> 07:14.533
- My apologies.
- <i>♪ [ Resumes ]</i>

07:42.895 --> 07:46.832
Are we ready?
Yes, I think so.

07:51.871 --> 07:54.606
Let me see your hands.

07:54.608 --> 07:56.875
Other side.

08:01.881 --> 08:05.717
So, did anything interesting
happen to anybody this week?

08:10.723 --> 08:11.790
No?

08:11.792 --> 08:17.996
So I'm the only one,
am I?
What, dear?

08:18.197 --> 08:21.132
I was going over
our accounts the other day,

08:21.134 --> 08:25.704
and it seems our factory had
its best quarter ever.

08:26.205 --> 08:28.974
And I was rather intrigued
to discover...

08:28.976 --> 08:31.610
that the items which were
moving most rapidly...

08:31.612 --> 08:35.881
were the new firework designs
by your brother.

08:38.251 --> 08:39.985
That's right.
[ Chuckles ]

08:39.986 --> 08:46.057
Not too long ago I had some
doubts that you had the stuff
to be my partner one day.

08:46.059 --> 08:49.194
But I'm very encouraged.

08:49.862 --> 08:52.197
Very encouraged.

08:52.532 --> 08:59.004
And by way of thanks,
I'd like you to say
the family grace today.

09:02.608 --> 09:06.778
Um, could we all
bow our heads?

09:06.780 --> 09:09.180
[ Woman Screams ]

09:11.217 --> 09:16.922
[ Screaming Continues ]
Jesus! Jesus!

09:20.860 --> 09:23.895
What is it, Bridgit?
[ Sobbing ]

09:23.897 --> 09:26.197
What's wrong?

09:36.175 --> 09:41.346
Oh, my God.
<i>[ Baby Crying ]</i>

09:44.183 --> 09:46.785
,
what did you do?
I--

09:46.787 --> 09:48.353
Answer me!
I didn't do nothin'.

09:48.355 --> 09:52.657
Then what is that child--
I was pouring out
the water from the vegetables,

09:52.659 --> 09:58.263
then there was a terrible
screamin' on the ground, and
I looks, and there was a baby!

09:58.265 --> 10:00.865
[ Continues Crying ]

10:06.372 --> 10:10.141
Call Dr. Mueller.
I'll do it.

10:14.113 --> 10:16.715
Where are you taking it?

10:16.717 --> 10:19.117
Not in the house?

10:26.926 --> 10:31.963
Well, he's breathing fine.
Heartbeat's strong.

10:31.965 --> 10:34.332
Seems like a healthy child.

10:34.334 --> 10:36.034
Is there anything
we should do?

10:36.036 --> 10:39.004
Well, keep him warm and dry,
and don't worry yourself.

10:39.006 --> 10:42.641
If he needs anything, he'll be
the first to let you know.

10:42.643 --> 10:46.645
He'll be fine.
Don't worry.
[ Knocking ]

10:52.818 --> 10:56.821
We found this one
hiding in a cellar
a few blocks away.

10:56.823 --> 10:59.190
She won't talk.

11:02.695 --> 11:04.396
You go on to your room.

11:04.398 --> 11:06.798
<i>[ Baby Fusses ]</i>
<i>Miss,</i>

11:06.800 --> 11:09.768
<i>is this your baby?</i>

11:16.175 --> 11:21.079
Lady, is this your baby
or isn't it?

11:23.716 --> 11:27.852
You wanna make life
easy for yourself
and tell us yes or no,

11:27.854 --> 11:32.290
or do you want me to ask
the doctor here to examine you?

11:33.392 --> 11:37.028
Doctor, do you mind?

11:37.329 --> 11:40.799
Could I have some privacy?

11:46.372 --> 11:51.710
Jim, would you
care for some tea?
No, no. That's all right.

11:54.113 --> 11:57.248
Quite a situation.

11:57.250 --> 11:59.718
Incredible.

12:00.486 --> 12:02.954
There you are.

12:02.956 --> 12:06.191
These niggers drop babies
like rabbits.

12:06.193 --> 12:11.229
Fellow runs off,
and, of course, the woman
tries to get rid of it.

12:11.231 --> 12:14.933
What's going to happen
to her?

12:15.067 --> 12:20.739
She'll get six to eight months--
child abuse, abandonment,

12:20.741 --> 12:22.507
<i>attempted murder.</i>

12:22.509 --> 12:25.844
And then she'll
get pregnant again.

12:26.011 --> 12:31.416
What'll happen to the baby?
<i>They've got places</i>
<i>for them.</i>

12:31.784 --> 12:36.121
Pickaninny farms, I call them.
[ Laughs ]

12:36.489 --> 12:40.925
Well, she's definitely
given birth recently.
That's about all I can tell you.

12:40.927 --> 12:42.894
I'll give you a report tomorrow.

12:42.896 --> 12:46.998
Sorry to see your Sunday dinner
disrupted like this, folks,

12:47.000 --> 12:50.101
and I guess I'd better be
getting back to mine.

12:50.103 --> 12:52.403
<i>Good day.</i>
<i>Good day, Doctor.</i>

12:52.405 --> 12:58.076
- Thank you, Doctor.
- We're going to need
your signature on this.

12:58.078 --> 13:03.014
Just a formality,
and then we'll take them
off your hands.

13:11.223 --> 13:16.461
Excuse me, dear.
Would you mind if I asked
the inspector a question?

13:16.463 --> 13:19.564
Oh, no.
No, you go ahead.

13:20.399 --> 13:23.568
She's going to be
put into prison, isn't she?

13:23.570 --> 13:27.238
- Oh, yes.
- Without her child?

13:27.240 --> 13:32.076
Well, a woman who abandons
her baby like this--

13:32.078 --> 13:35.980
I think it would be better
for the baby if they were
separated, don't you?

13:35.982 --> 13:40.919
- <i>We're not dealing</i>
<i> with Christians, ma'am.</i>
<i>- Exactly.</i>

13:41.086 --> 13:45.857
<i>These people don't have</i>
<i>the same sense of family</i>
<i>as what we do.</i>

13:45.859 --> 13:48.059
Exactly.

13:49.161 --> 13:55.200
Would it make
any difference in her case
if we were to take her in?

13:57.236 --> 13:59.270
Temporarily, of course.

13:59.272 --> 14:01.439
Dear, you don't mean--

14:01.441 --> 14:03.441
Nobody's even talked to her.

14:03.443 --> 14:08.379
Nobody knows what
made her do it. If we knew,
maybe we could help her.

14:08.381 --> 14:09.614
If, if, if, if.

14:09.616 --> 14:14.619
- I'm just asking.
- It's out of the question.

14:14.954 --> 14:21.059
My wife is
a very generous woman,
which I appreciate.

14:23.629 --> 14:28.533
Excuse us for just a moment,
would you?

14:52.658 --> 14:55.526
My wife wants
the statue down.

14:56.629 --> 14:59.130
Right, Evie?

15:02.902 --> 15:05.169
Right, Evie?

15:05.638 --> 15:07.272
Yes, dear, yes.

15:07.274 --> 15:09.274
Yes, what?
Tell them.

15:09.276 --> 15:13.177
[ Shouting ]
Tell them!
What do you want?

15:13.312 --> 15:16.681
Yes, I want
the statue down, please.

15:16.683 --> 15:20.218
- See?
- <i>Yes, Mr. Thaw.</i>

15:20.220 --> 15:22.353
We quite understand
your feelings in the matter.

15:22.355 --> 15:28.059
No. Look, uh,
he put that statue up there
to make me look like a fool.

15:28.227 --> 15:30.929
<i>I'm Harry K. Thaw</i>
<i>of Pittsburgh!</i>

15:30.931 --> 15:33.031
I've got my reputation
to think about.

15:33.033 --> 15:36.534
I'm not havin' my wife
on public display!

15:36.536 --> 15:39.570
Of course not,
Mr. Thaw.

15:40.072 --> 15:45.510
Now, uh, regarding
the possible grounds
for legal action--

15:45.512 --> 15:48.479
Exactly! Legal grounds.
Now you're talkin'.

15:48.481 --> 15:51.149
There aren't any,
Mr. Thaw.

15:51.151 --> 15:53.318
What the hell
are you talking about?

15:53.320 --> 15:58.589
You're lawyers. Find some.
For God's sake, she's my wife!

15:58.591 --> 16:03.027
She's not a chorus girl anymore.
She's not a model.

16:03.029 --> 16:05.296
She's not his mistress.
She's my wife!

16:05.298 --> 16:09.133
I want you to do whatever
the hell you have to do to get
my wife off that building.

16:09.135 --> 16:15.573
Yes, Mr. Thaw.
We'll do everything we can...
within the realm of the law.

16:18.210 --> 16:21.346
Because if you don't--

16:22.581 --> 16:24.615
[ Horn Honking ]

16:24.617 --> 16:28.219
♪ [ Upbeat ]

16:35.627 --> 16:38.730
♪ I've heard men say so often
they could love
their wives alone ♪

16:38.732 --> 16:43.368
♪ But I think that
such foolish men must have
hearts made of stone ♪

16:43.370 --> 16:47.405
♪ Now, my heart is made
of softer stuff
It melts at each warm glance ♪

16:47.407 --> 16:52.276
<i>♪ A pretty girl can't</i>
<i>  look my way</i>
<i>  without a new romance ♪</i>

16:52.278 --> 16:58.116
♪ Oh, I could love
a million girls
with every girl, a twin ♪

16:58.118 --> 17:02.053
♪ I could love a Chinese girl
an Eskimo, a Finn ♪

17:02.055 --> 17:06.124
♪ I could love a German girl
a girl with golden curls ♪

17:06.126 --> 17:09.660
♪ In fact I think
that I could love
about a million girls ♪

17:09.662 --> 17:14.232
[ Chorus ]
♪ He could love a million girls
a million girls, could he ♪

17:14.233 --> 17:17.568
♪ I could love a native girl
from far across the sea ♪

17:17.569 --> 17:23.107
- <i>♪ He could love a redhead girl</i>
<i>    a girl with raven curls ♪</i>
<i>-[ Applause ]</i>

17:23.108 --> 17:28.813
♪ In fact I think
that I could love
about a million girls ♪

17:36.288 --> 17:40.792
Harry,
are you a little warm?

17:40.794 --> 17:45.430
<i>Do you want to</i>
<i>take off your coat?</i>
<i>I'm fine.</i>

17:46.165 --> 17:47.698
I'm cool as a cucumber.

17:47.700 --> 17:53.204
♪ Oh, I could love
a million girls
with every girl, a twin ♪

17:53.206 --> 17:57.608
♪ I could love a Chinese girl
an Eskimo, a Finn ♪

17:57.610 --> 18:01.412
♪ I could love a German girl
a girl with golden curls ♪

18:01.414 --> 18:05.683
♪ In fact I think
that I could love
about a million girls ♪

18:05.685 --> 18:10.088
♪ He could love a million girls
a million girls, could he ♪

18:10.090 --> 18:14.225
♪ I could love a native girl
from far across the sea ♪

18:14.227 --> 18:17.462
♪ He could love a redhead girl
a girl with raven curls ♪

18:17.464 --> 18:20.598
I'll be back in a minute.
<i>Harry.</i>

18:20.600 --> 18:22.767
Harry.

18:25.637 --> 18:30.141
♪ I loved a girl
whose eyes shone forth
just like a crystal mass ♪

18:30.143 --> 18:34.112
♪ I loved her
till I found out that
her eye was made of glass ♪

18:34.114 --> 18:38.449
♪ I loved a girl
whose form it was
a gorgeous thing to see ♪

18:38.451 --> 18:42.687
♪ I loved her till I found out
that part of it was a tree ♪

18:42.689 --> 18:48.893
♪ Oh, I could love
a million girls
with every girl, a twin ♪

18:48.895 --> 18:52.897
♪ I could love a Chinese girl
an Eskimo, a Finn ♪

18:52.899 --> 18:56.467
♪ I could love a German girl
a girl with golden curls ♪

18:56.469 --> 19:00.705
<i>♪ In fact I think</i>
<i>  that I could love</i>
<i>  about a million girls ♪</i>

19:00.707 --> 19:05.309
♪ He could love a million girls
a million girls, could he ♪

19:05.311 --> 19:09.413
♪ I could love a native girl
from far across the sea ♪
White!

19:09.415 --> 19:12.183
♪ He could love a redhead girl
a girl with raven curls ♪

19:12.185 --> 19:18.823
-♪ In fact I think that I could
love about a million girls ♪
-[ Screaming ]

19:20.759 --> 19:23.227
[ Crowd Screaming ]

19:23.229 --> 19:26.764
- [ Gasping ]
- <i>[ Screaming Continues ]</i>

19:26.766 --> 19:29.400
♪ [ Stops ]

19:31.904 --> 19:35.239
[ Screams ]

19:35.440 --> 19:38.843
[ Crowd Screaming,
Glass Shattering ]

19:45.484 --> 19:50.588
[ Woman With White ]
Help him! Help!
Help him!

19:50.590 --> 19:55.359
- Help him!
- Hey! Hey, you!

19:55.361 --> 20:00.598
All right. Now, don't do
anything stupid.

20:00.600 --> 20:04.468
J-Just give me the gun.

20:05.771 --> 20:10.975
[ Sobbing ]
[ Man ]
Get a doctor! Get a doctor!

20:18.684 --> 20:21.919
Aw, Harry! Harry!

20:21.921 --> 20:25.890
<i>Harry! Harry.</i>

20:27.492 --> 20:29.660
Harry!

20:31.763 --> 20:35.333
♪ [ Piano, Slow Waltz ]

20:35.335 --> 20:41.872
♪

21:52.511 --> 21:55.780
♪ [ Ends ]

21:56.648 --> 22:00.518
<i>Oh, well, do you</i>
<i>want to know everything?</i>

22:00.520 --> 22:03.554
Please.

22:04.956 --> 22:07.925
Well, all right.

22:09.027 --> 22:10.661
He had these whips.

22:10.663 --> 22:14.965
<i>This was in this castle</i>
<i>in Austria that he took me</i>
<i>for vacation.</i>

22:14.967 --> 22:18.002
<i>Well, he put me in a room,</i>
<i>and he locked the door.</i>

22:18.004 --> 22:21.806
And then he told me
that if I made any noise
that he'd do something to me--

22:21.808 --> 22:23.507
something terrible.
Wait just a minute.

22:23.509 --> 22:29.947
Whom are you talking about?
You're talking about
Stanford White!

22:30.115 --> 22:32.883
[ Stammering ]
Oh, no, no, no, no.

22:32.885 --> 22:37.355
No. No-- Stanny?
Stanny would never do
anything like this.

22:37.357 --> 22:40.658
<i>He was lovely.</i>
<i>Lovely man.</i>

22:40.660 --> 22:42.093
He admired me--

22:42.095 --> 22:43.594
No, I'm talking about
Harry, my husband.

22:43.596 --> 22:49.100
- Nonsense! My Harry would
never do anything like that.
- Just a minute, Mrs. Thaw.

22:49.102 --> 22:54.605
- <i>What you're saying is,</i>
<i>  your husband did all this.</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

22:54.607 --> 22:58.075
He had a whip,
a kind of a...

22:58.077 --> 23:00.678
dog whip, and he started
to beat me with it.

23:00.680 --> 23:03.481
I fail to see what this has to
do with the defense of my son.

23:03.483 --> 23:08.085
Mrs. Thaw, you don't understand.
We have got to prove
that your son was insane!

23:08.087 --> 23:10.388
My son is not insane!

23:10.390 --> 23:12.556
Insane at the time
of the murder, Mrs. Thaw--

23:12.558 --> 23:16.827
I'm sorry. But there <i>is</i>
<i>a world of difference.</i>

23:16.829 --> 23:20.398
There's nothing wrong
with Harry.

23:20.400 --> 23:22.767
All right, Mrs. Thaw.

23:22.769 --> 23:23.801
That's fine.

23:23.803 --> 23:27.538
Your son will be convicted
of murder in the first degree.

23:27.540 --> 23:28.839
He will be executed
accordingly,

23:28.841 --> 23:33.811
and, if that's what
you've hired me to accomplish,
I'll be very happy to oblige.

23:33.813 --> 23:35.813
He was perfectly all right
until he married her.

23:35.815 --> 23:40.885
- She's the only thing
wrong with my son!
- Ha! That's a laugh!

23:40.887 --> 23:45.523
All right,
stop it, both of you.
Stop it right now!

23:45.690 --> 23:49.193
Mrs. Thaw,
would you be kind enough
to leave me alone with Evelyn?

23:49.195 --> 23:52.696
With pleasure,
Mr. Delmas.

24:00.005 --> 24:02.640
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

24:04.509 --> 24:06.877
[ Clears Throat ]

24:07.045 --> 24:12.082
You know, Evelyn,
Mrs. Thaw <i>is</i>
<i>a very generous woman.</i>

24:12.851 --> 24:15.553
Ha, that's another laugh.

24:16.888 --> 24:23.194
You don't really want to see
your husband electrocuted,
do you?

24:24.796 --> 24:26.230
[ Sighs ]

24:26.232 --> 24:30.768
I guess not.
He <i>is</i> crazy, though,
you know.

24:30.770 --> 24:34.104
Mrs. Thaw is prepared
to offer you
a substantial sum of money...

24:34.106 --> 24:37.575
if you will
cooperate fully with us.

24:38.176 --> 24:44.181
- What do you mean?
- I mean, if you testify
as directed in court,

24:44.183 --> 24:46.517
and if the trial ends
successfully--

24:46.519 --> 24:51.088
for us, that is--
you will agree to divorce him.

24:51.090 --> 24:53.791
Divorce Harry?
Are you kidding?

24:53.793 --> 24:57.127
Oh, there's a great deal
of money involved.

24:57.129 --> 25:02.166
- Yeah?
- A great, great deal.

25:02.168 --> 25:04.768
How much?

25:04.770 --> 25:08.239
One million dollars.

25:14.045 --> 25:19.617
Now, you say
that Mr. Stanford White
beat you with a whip?

25:19.619 --> 25:21.018
Yes.

25:21.020 --> 25:24.154
A horsewhip.
[ Crowd Murmurs ]

25:28.560 --> 25:30.561
<i>[ Gavel Pounds ]</i>

25:30.563 --> 25:31.195
A horsewhip?
Yes.

25:31.197 --> 25:35.733
You say also that he gave you
a drink that was drugged.
Is that right?

25:35.735 --> 25:38.536
Yes.

25:39.037 --> 25:43.874
Was this before
or after the whipping?

25:58.623 --> 26:01.692
Well, I don't remember.

26:02.694 --> 26:04.762
He wanted to have
his way with me,

26:04.764 --> 26:07.197
so he drugged me,
and then he whipped me.

26:07.199 --> 26:12.836
[ Crowd Murmurs ]
<i>[ Judge ]</i>
<i>Order! Order!</i>

26:12.838 --> 26:17.875
And you suddenly remembered
this horrible story,

26:17.877 --> 26:21.045
decided to tell your husband
about it three years later...

26:21.047 --> 26:28.152
on the very night
that you knew he was most likely
to encounter Mr. White...

26:28.154 --> 26:31.822
at Madison Square Garden.

26:33.358 --> 26:36.860
- Is that right?
- Yes.

26:38.863 --> 26:41.098
No more questions,
Your Honor.

26:41.100 --> 26:43.701
[ Crowd Clamoring ]

26:46.304 --> 26:49.807
Could you
stay behind that car?

27:33.685 --> 27:38.155
- What's the matter?
- It's not
a very pretty sight, ma'am.

27:55.907 --> 28:00.944
[ Yiddish Accent ] Missus.
Here, here! Missus, here!
It's face cutting.

28:00.946 --> 28:06.050
Missus. Missus!
Come, please. Come!

28:06.718 --> 28:09.420
Missus, come.

28:09.422 --> 28:13.957
<i>If you wanted to see,</i>
<i>you have to, uh, to see.</i>

28:13.959 --> 28:16.126
Come.

28:17.028 --> 28:23.434
- Yes, that's pretty.
- This-- it cost
about ten cents. Yeah?

28:23.768 --> 28:28.839
What can be cheaper?
Missus, very expensive.
Make a discount.

28:29.908 --> 28:31.341
Sit down.

28:31.343 --> 28:35.112
Very pretty, huh?
You are very pretty.

28:35.114 --> 28:38.916
Thank you.
Uh, this way, your body.

28:39.084 --> 28:42.319
Go! It's good.
Down-- uh, to.

28:42.321 --> 28:45.789
Oh.
It's good. Okay?

28:46.057 --> 28:49.393
Keep your face out.
This girl is my daughter.
She's beautiful.

28:49.395 --> 28:51.895
Please, uh, like this.

28:51.897 --> 28:54.231
She's wonderful.

28:54.233 --> 28:56.400
Yeah.

28:58.336 --> 29:02.406
She's uh--
Please, keep your face.
Keep your face.

29:02.408 --> 29:05.509
She's, uh, wonderful.

29:06.177 --> 29:13.117
- <i>Why is she on a string?</i>
<i>- She's, uh,</i>
<i>  very beautiful, yes?</i>

29:14.385 --> 29:17.855
Keep-Keep--
Why is she
tied up on a rope?

29:17.857 --> 29:20.090
Why do you have her
tied up?
Oh.

29:20.092 --> 29:24.428
Uh, I have to be sure
she will, uh, be not kidnapped.

29:24.796 --> 29:28.899
Uh, will do her better
if she'll be connected with me.

29:28.901 --> 29:31.068
Keep your face.
[ Man ]
Hey!

29:31.070 --> 29:33.103
- Hey!
- Go away, you.

29:33.105 --> 29:35.973
- A word! A word, please!
- Go your own way.

29:35.975 --> 29:42.146
- A very, very important
word for you!
- <i>Do you see I am very busy?</i>

29:48.019 --> 29:51.522
I don't believe it.
Go your own way.

29:51.524 --> 29:55.392
- <i>We don't make up--</i>
<i>- Go away, huh?</i>

29:55.394 --> 29:58.295
[ Shouting ]
Will you go?
Will you go away?

29:58.297 --> 30:03.467
You see I make a business?
Go away! Go away!

30:06.371 --> 30:09.439
[ Speaking Yiddish ]

30:16.047 --> 30:20.117
Do something, uh, for me--

30:20.119 --> 30:23.520
Only one five minute.
Only one--

30:23.522 --> 30:26.356
one two minute.

30:37.302 --> 30:40.938
[ Foreign Language ]

31:10.869 --> 31:12.069
<i>[ Woman Screams ]</i>

31:12.071 --> 31:16.206
<i>[ Man, Woman Shouting</i>
<i>  In Foreign Language ]</i>

31:16.208 --> 31:17.941
<i>[ Shouting, Laughing ]</i>

31:17.943 --> 31:24.114
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>My God, my God!</i>
<i>What the hell you--</i>

31:35.326 --> 31:38.528
<i>[ Women Shouting ]</i>

31:42.533 --> 31:45.602
Katela, come. Come!

32:04.122 --> 32:07.257
<i>Meshuggeneh! Meshuggeneh!</i>

32:07.259 --> 32:11.461
[ Continuing In Yiddish ]

32:12.463 --> 32:18.001
Where do you get
the chutzpah to judge me?

32:18.003 --> 32:20.570
[ Screaming ]

32:22.640 --> 32:27.411
[ Shouting ]
[ All Chattering ]

32:35.586 --> 32:40.057
[ Wife Shrieking ]

33:00.511 --> 33:07.317
<i>What do you give me?</i>
<i>Nothing but tsuris!</i>

33:08.319 --> 33:13.090
- [ Speaking Yiddish ]
- [ Wailing ]

33:14.425 --> 33:17.527
♪ [ Ragtime Piano ]

33:17.529 --> 33:27.771
♪

33:28.139 --> 33:32.542
<i>Thank you,</i>
<i>that was very nice.</i>
<i>We'll let you know.</i>

33:32.544 --> 33:34.778
<i>Next.</i>

33:37.382 --> 33:42.119
<i>What's your name?</i>
<i>Coalhouse Walker, Jr.</i>

33:42.286 --> 33:47.624
- Where've you been playing?
- Oh, here and there.

33:48.593 --> 33:52.262
It's a band job, you know,
not a solo act.

33:52.264 --> 33:57.667
- If it's regular work,
I'm interested.
- Okay, let's hear you.

33:57.669 --> 34:00.137
Yes, sir.

34:00.705 --> 34:04.307
♪ [ Melodic ]

34:16.387 --> 34:19.822
♪ [ Continues ]

35:06.804 --> 35:10.640
You know this book
what I have given you?

35:10.642 --> 35:15.178
We have a lack in money.
Give me back this book.

35:15.180 --> 35:18.849
I like it very much.
I make you another.

35:18.851 --> 35:22.652
Just like this one?
The same.

35:24.822 --> 35:26.523
Promise?
Promise.

35:26.525 --> 35:30.527
If you give it to me,
I'll be proud with you, huh?

35:44.642 --> 35:49.913
- Hmm.
- Now try do it--
try do it myself.

35:49.915 --> 35:52.349
I, uh--

35:52.917 --> 35:55.719
Oh, I see. Yeah.

35:55.721 --> 35:57.220
You like it?

35:57.222 --> 35:59.322
Well, it's-it's-it's
very interesting.

35:59.324 --> 36:06.263
Where did you get this thing?
I do it, alone,
with my hands.

36:06.265 --> 36:09.366
I've create.
You got any others?

36:09.368 --> 36:14.738
I can do once more.
I can do everything--
what do your heart desire.

36:14.740 --> 36:19.242
What do you want
for this thing?
All right.

36:19.244 --> 36:25.382
I'll give you four dollars
if you agree not to
take this idea anywhere else...

36:25.384 --> 36:28.952
and 40 cents for each one
you make for me.

36:54.779 --> 36:58.548
Thank you, ladies and gentlemen.
It's my pleasure
to introduce to you...

36:58.550 --> 37:05.255
the newest and bluest member
of the Clef Club band,
Professor Coalhouse Walker, Jr.

37:05.257 --> 37:07.457
Play!

37:51.402 --> 37:57.507
Where is that man that usually
sells silhouettes here--
you know, with the little girl?

37:57.675 --> 38:00.944
Oh, yes. Thank you.
This is it.

38:00.946 --> 38:03.747
[ Horn Honking ]
Ma'am!

38:03.749 --> 38:06.449
Ma'am, I can't stop here.
We're blocking traffic.

38:06.451 --> 38:10.954
That's all right.
You can go back.
I'll be back later.

38:36.947 --> 38:39.649
<i>[ Knocking ]</i>

38:58.736 --> 39:03.573
- [ Screams ]
- No, no, no, no.
Please, please don't scream.

39:03.575 --> 39:06.643
You don't have to be afraid.
I am not going to hurt you.

39:06.645 --> 39:10.714
Don't you move! You stay
right there! You stop! Stop!
I'm not...

39:10.716 --> 39:13.083
<i>gonna hurt you,</i>
<i>I just--</i>

39:13.085 --> 39:15.819
I mean, you probably think
I'm a--

39:15.821 --> 39:22.759
<i>I don't know, but I'm not.</i>
<i>I'm a businessman.</i>
<i>I design fireworks.</i>

39:23.094 --> 39:27.997
- This is my card.
- Don't come near me.
Don't come near me.

39:29.600 --> 39:33.603
I, uh-- I actually work
for my brother-in-law.
He owns the factory.

39:33.605 --> 39:37.607
But I'll be made
a full partner soon,
and then when he retires,

39:37.609 --> 39:39.542
the company will go to me.

39:39.544 --> 39:43.113
We do flags--
uh, flag buntings,

39:43.115 --> 39:46.015
trims, trophies, medals--
anything for public occasions.

39:46.017 --> 39:51.855
You can see where it says
on the card here "consultants
for public occasions."

39:51.857 --> 39:55.825
<i>But fireworks is actually</i>
<i>our biggest line.</i>

39:55.827 --> 39:58.995
Please take it.

40:10.808 --> 40:12.475
What do you want?

40:12.477 --> 40:16.012
Well, I want-- if you have
an evening free, I--

40:16.014 --> 40:21.518
<i>I know you're very busy,</i>
<i>but if you do have</i>
<i>an evening free,</i>

40:21.520 --> 40:25.688
and you would like to,
uh, do-- go--

40:25.690 --> 40:32.061
I would very much like
to escort you to something.

40:33.798 --> 40:35.799
No, no, no, no.
Please keep it.

40:35.801 --> 40:41.538
I have more.
So, what do you say?
[ Clears Throat ]

40:42.573 --> 40:46.209
Are you some kind
of a lunatic now?

40:47.578 --> 40:50.880
I'm sorry.
I'm acting like one,
aren't I?

40:50.882 --> 40:54.984
You should see me
at the office.
I am really not like this.

40:54.986 --> 41:00.857
So, what do you say?
Do you have some free time?

41:03.894 --> 41:06.095
Well,

41:07.765 --> 41:09.165
maybe.

41:09.167 --> 41:12.836
You are?
I mean, might be.

41:14.572 --> 41:18.708
I-- I mean, when?

41:20.244 --> 41:22.812
What about right now?

41:22.814 --> 41:25.181
Right now? You mean--

41:25.183 --> 41:29.619
- Do you mean, just--
- Well, is there something wrong
with right now?

41:29.621 --> 41:33.223
<i>No! No, no, no, no.</i>
<i>It's just-- It's just--</i>

41:33.225 --> 41:37.927
[ Sighs ]
No. Nothing.
Now is fine.

41:39.797 --> 41:41.798
So...

41:41.800 --> 41:45.869
escort me... something.
[ Giggles ]

41:45.871 --> 41:48.705
[ Chiming ]

41:49.840 --> 41:54.978
<i>Dear, we're going</i>
<i>to eat without him.</i>

41:54.980 --> 41:57.113
Son, sit down.

41:57.115 --> 42:00.550
Come.
Everyone sit down.

42:00.552 --> 42:02.752
Come.

42:08.526 --> 42:11.895
Don't worry, dear.
He'll be back.

42:12.196 --> 42:18.735
<i>.</i>
<i>If anybody should be worried,</i>
<i>it's me, isn't it? And I'm not.</i>

42:20.704 --> 42:21.771
Yes.

42:21.773 --> 42:25.708
You know
what he's like sometimes.
It's just his age.

42:25.710 --> 42:28.645
Everybody goes through this.

42:28.812 --> 42:34.117
<i>Three days!</i>
<i>He hasn't slept at home</i>
<i>in three days.</i>

42:34.585 --> 42:37.186
He hasn't even
been at work.

42:37.555 --> 42:43.293
He hasn't had the common
courtesy to telephone us and
let us know if he's all right.

42:45.095 --> 42:51.167
- Has he been
in touch with you?
- Wouldn't I have told you?

42:51.869 --> 42:54.671
I-- Yes.
Of course you would.

42:54.673 --> 42:56.806
I--

42:57.841 --> 43:01.210
Let us bow our heads.
[ Sighs ]

43:01.679 --> 43:07.317
<i>For what we are about</i>
<i>to receive, dear Lord,</i>
<i>we give thanks.</i>

43:08.919 --> 43:12.155
[ Door Chimes Ring ]

43:14.124 --> 43:18.161
I'll get it.
No.
No, you stay right there.

43:20.831 --> 43:23.833
<i>I'll take care of this.</i>

43:33.177 --> 43:38.748
Good afternoon.
I wonder if you might
be able to help me.

43:38.750 --> 43:39.983
Uh-- what do you want?

43:39.985 --> 43:43.353
Well, I'm looking for
a young woman of color
called Sarah.

43:43.355 --> 43:46.990
I'm told she was
taken in to this house.

43:46.992 --> 43:49.659
Uh, who are you?
Oh, I'm sorry.

43:49.661 --> 43:52.028
My name is
Coalhouse Walker, Jr.

43:52.030 --> 43:57.834
Are you a-a-a relative?
I wouldn't exactly say that.

43:57.836 --> 44:04.007
Well, what shall I tell her
is the reason for your visit?

44:04.141 --> 44:08.111
Just tell her
that Mr. Walker would
like to have a word with her.

44:08.113 --> 44:11.714
Would you please
wait around the back?

44:20.858 --> 44:24.193
There's a colored gentleman
downstairs.

44:24.195 --> 44:28.031
He says he wants
to have a word with you.

44:29.333 --> 44:35.438
Well, I th--
think you'd better
go down and talk to him.

44:39.810 --> 44:42.445
- Are you going to go down?
- No, sir.

44:42.447 --> 44:48.151
Well, that's, uh,
not very good, is it?

44:48.285 --> 44:51.387
<i>But the man seems to have</i>
<i>some connection with you,</i>

44:51.389 --> 44:55.825
and I think I'd like
to know what it is.

45:00.431 --> 45:04.333
Dear, she doesn't want
to talk to him.

45:05.202 --> 45:07.370
I see.

45:07.905 --> 45:11.874
And I suppose
that's the end of it?
Would--

45:12.843 --> 45:15.978
[ Sighing ]
I-- Yes, yes.

45:19.149 --> 45:20.216
[ Laughing ]

45:20.218 --> 45:25.121
You're just as sweet
as you can be.
Yes, you are.

45:25.123 --> 45:27.223
That's my child.

45:29.026 --> 45:33.463
Excuse me, but I don't believe
anyone invited you in.

45:34.131 --> 45:37.200
This is my child.

45:37.202 --> 45:42.371
- This is a cute little devil,
isn't he?
- [ Cooing ]

45:42.973 --> 45:47.210
- It is a boy, isn't it?
- Yes.

45:48.746 --> 45:51.380
So you're the father.

45:52.249 --> 45:53.783
Yeah.

45:53.785 --> 45:57.887
Where's Sarah?
She doesn't want to see you.

45:58.922 --> 46:00.356
[ Baby Cooing ]

46:00.358 --> 46:04.994
Stubborn woman, Sarah.
Very stubborn.

46:05.429 --> 46:11.334
Well, you tell her
I'll be back real soon,
okay?

46:11.336 --> 46:15.104
And my apologies
for the intrusion.
Good afternoon.

46:15.106 --> 46:18.074
[ Cooing Continues ]

46:18.076 --> 46:20.843
[ Laughing ]

46:23.046 --> 46:26.382
<i>[ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>
<i>All rise!</i>

46:52.943 --> 46:57.914
Gentlemen of the jury,
have you come to a verdict?

46:57.916 --> 47:01.317
Yes, Your Honor,
we have.

47:01.919 --> 47:06.889
We find the defendant
not guilty of murder
in the first degree...

47:06.891 --> 47:09.392
by reason of insanity.

47:09.394 --> 47:11.928
[ All Murmur ]

47:14.164 --> 47:16.432
I'm crazy?
[ Gavel Pounds ]

47:16.434 --> 47:18.467
Goddamn it,
they think I'm crazy!

47:18.469 --> 47:22.605
Mr. Thaw,
will you please stand?

47:27.311 --> 47:29.979
You have heard
the verdict.

47:29.981 --> 47:34.150
Normally,
in such a case as this,
the bench would retire.

47:34.152 --> 47:39.889
But I think in this instance
I would have to be
out of my mind...

47:39.891 --> 47:42.925
not to recommend that you be
sent to the asylum...

47:42.927 --> 47:45.962
for the criminally insane
at Matteawan...

47:45.964 --> 47:48.998
until such time as duly
constituted medical opinion...

47:49.000 --> 47:55.404
determines that you are
no longer dangerous
to the public at large.

47:55.406 --> 47:57.273
Yes!
[ All Murmur ]

47:57.275 --> 48:01.310
[ Gavel Pounding ]
Order. Order.

48:01.312 --> 48:06.883
Mr. Thaw,
do you have anything to say?

48:09.119 --> 48:11.988
Uh,

48:15.893 --> 48:19.228
this whole trial
has been a fiasco.

48:19.230 --> 48:25.968
Now, Mr. Thaw, please limit
your remarks to the statement
that I have just made.

48:25.970 --> 48:28.604
No, listen to me.
No, no. Uh--

48:28.606 --> 48:34.377
I'm as sane
as any man in this room!
[ All Murmur ]

48:35.679 --> 48:39.048
You're the ones
that are insane!

48:39.050 --> 48:40.316
This case is closed.

48:40.318 --> 48:46.355
And you heard the testimony!
She was 16 years old!
He drugged her!

48:46.357 --> 48:48.557
God, he ruined my wife!

48:48.559 --> 48:51.327
He whipped her,
for God's sake!

48:51.329 --> 48:54.030
She was 16 years old!

48:54.032 --> 48:57.366
The man was a beast!
You should thank me!

48:57.368 --> 49:00.703
Where's your sense of morality?

49:02.005 --> 49:05.174
I did the law a favor!

49:05.176 --> 49:09.045
[ Crowd Clamoring ]

49:09.047 --> 49:14.417
[ All Shouting, Indistinct ]

49:32.569 --> 49:37.606
It's right over there!
Look at that!

49:41.244 --> 49:43.612
Evelyn! Evelyn!

50:03.600 --> 50:07.036
[ Drunkenly ]
So what should I do?
Nothing! Absolutely nothing.

50:07.038 --> 50:10.006
- We will do
everything for you.
- We'll take care of it all.

50:10.008 --> 50:14.243
You'll teach me routines?
He is the dance teacher.

50:14.245 --> 50:16.712
He's the manager!
No, no, I am the manager.

50:16.714 --> 50:22.651
He is the dance instructor.
This is your agent,
and he is your lawyer.

50:22.653 --> 50:26.222
All of us for one person,
for Evelyn.

50:26.224 --> 50:29.325
That's all we care about.
This little piggy
went to market.

50:29.327 --> 50:33.529
This little piggy went home.
This little piggy
had roast beef,

50:33.531 --> 50:35.664
and this little piggy--

50:35.666 --> 50:40.202
this little piggy
went wee-wee-wee-wee...

50:40.204 --> 50:45.041
all the way to the bank!
[ Laughing ]

50:45.242 --> 50:48.044
♪ [ Singing, Indistinct ]

51:00.323 --> 51:02.558
Evelyn?

51:02.560 --> 51:06.462
Oh! Oh, sweetheart!

51:06.464 --> 51:09.065
Where--
where have you been?

51:09.067 --> 51:12.768
I'm so--
Oh, you waited for me.
Yes.

51:12.770 --> 51:16.705
You waited for me
all this time.

51:21.411 --> 51:24.180
What were their names?
What?

51:24.182 --> 51:26.715
Sorry.
What were their names?
Whose names?

51:26.717 --> 51:30.686
The names
of the people you just
spent the evening with.

51:32.422 --> 51:35.124
Uh--
[ Laughs ]

51:35.126 --> 51:36.792
I forget!
What?

51:36.794 --> 51:39.562
I can't remember.
[ Laughs ]
Evelyn,

51:39.564 --> 51:45.501
these people are supposed
to decide your future,
and you forgot their names?

51:45.503 --> 51:48.404
Ohhh.

51:48.406 --> 51:50.272
Sweetheart.

51:50.274 --> 51:52.341
Will you open
the champagne?
Sure.

51:52.343 --> 51:58.180
I'll be right back.
One's an agent, one's a lawyer,
one's a manager.

51:58.182 --> 52:01.283
I don't know.
They're so cute.
They're just adorable.

52:01.285 --> 52:04.787
You know what I think
you should do? I think
you should find out their names,

52:04.789 --> 52:10.459
and then I'll have
my lawyers check to see
if they're legitimate.

52:10.461 --> 52:13.362
Evelyn, are you listening?

52:13.364 --> 52:14.797
Mm-hmm.

52:14.799 --> 52:17.733
You can't be too careful
just now, you know.

52:17.735 --> 52:23.639
<i>You never know</i>
<i>when someone might try</i>
<i>to take advantage of you.</i>

52:23.641 --> 52:25.541
Whoops!

52:25.543 --> 52:29.745
All my clothes went away.

52:29.747 --> 52:32.381
[ Giggling ]

52:37.621 --> 52:38.420
[ Clears Throat ]

52:38.422 --> 52:42.758
Sorry to interrupt.
It's unfortunate timing,
I know, but we had no choice,

52:42.760 --> 52:45.628
as you'll see
when you read this.

52:45.630 --> 52:48.397
Now, uh, look it over,
and sign at the bottom.

52:48.399 --> 52:51.767
If there's anything
you don't understand,
just feel free to ask.

52:51.769 --> 52:56.772
Gentlemen, this is
a private residence,
and your presence here--

52:56.774 --> 53:01.677
Shh! Now, wait a minute!
Stop! What is this?

53:01.811 --> 53:05.181
- What's that, Mrs. Thaw?
- Number four.

53:05.183 --> 53:08.684
"In compensation for my agreeing
to divorce Mr. Harold K. Thaw,

53:08.686 --> 53:12.521
I shall receive a sum
of $25,000"? What's that?

53:12.523 --> 53:15.391
I think that's clear enough.

53:15.892 --> 53:17.893
Oh, no. No!

53:17.895 --> 53:21.664
They are not pulling
that one on me.

53:21.965 --> 53:26.902
I'm getting a million or
forget it. You were there when
they said I'd get a million.

53:26.904 --> 53:30.539
That was when you were
suing him for divorce.

53:30.541 --> 53:35.878
It's quite a different matter
now that you're an adulteress,

53:36.646 --> 53:38.314
and he is suing you.

53:38.316 --> 53:40.516
What-- Harry suing <i>me</i>
<i>for divorce?</i>

53:40.518 --> 53:46.989
Well, Mr. Thaw is no longer
mentally competent. His mother
is making his decisions now.

53:48.725 --> 53:50.492
I saved his life, damn it!

53:50.494 --> 53:56.232
<i>If I hadn't testified,</i>
<i>he would have gone</i>
<i>to the electric chair!</i>

53:56.234 --> 54:00.536
I would have been a widow
with all of his money!
She knows that!

54:00.538 --> 54:06.375
- Mrs. Thaw--
- I earned that million dollars!
I want a million dollars!

54:06.377 --> 54:10.412
Mrs. Thaw, adultery is
a very serious charge
in a divorce proceeding.

54:10.414 --> 54:16.485
If you sign this now, you'll get
$25,000, and the divorce'll be
handled very quickly.

54:16.487 --> 54:20.489
If you don't sign it,
the chances are you'll wind up
with nothing at all.

54:20.491 --> 54:24.293
Now, you've got five minutes
to make up your mind.

54:24.295 --> 54:26.028
<i>I don't know</i>
<i>what this is all about,</i>

54:26.030 --> 54:30.266
<i>but I do know that what</i>
<i>you are doing here is</i>
<i>completely illegal.</i>

54:30.268 --> 54:34.870
<i>This is trespassing,</i>
<i>improper serving</i>
<i>of legal documents,</i>

54:34.872 --> 54:37.439
and before it goes any further,
I think you should leave.

54:37.441 --> 54:40.876
And I will have my lawyers
contact you in the morning.

54:40.878 --> 54:43.779
Well, who's got a pen?

54:43.913 --> 54:46.949
Evelyn, don't.
Don't sign it.
You don't have to.

54:46.951 --> 54:50.686
I could get my lawyers
to handle it.
When do I get the money?

54:50.688 --> 54:54.590
It's right here-- cash.

55:10.607 --> 55:14.677
Sorry to interrupt.
Good night.

55:21.351 --> 55:23.919
This is incredible.

55:24.087 --> 55:26.388
You shouldn't have
signed it, Evelyn.
You shouldn't have.

55:26.390 --> 55:30.693
Honey,
I don't want to have anything
to do them him anymore.

55:30.695 --> 55:35.064
That whole family has been
all over my back for years!

55:35.066 --> 55:37.399
Now I have the money.
I just want to forget it.

55:37.401 --> 55:41.537
- But they are using you.
- So we're even.

55:41.539 --> 55:43.372
Look, I can't let you
do this to yourself.

55:43.374 --> 55:48.110
You have to have
competent legal advice
from people you can trust.

55:48.112 --> 55:50.913
- Like who?
- I'll get my company's
lawyers to handle it.

55:50.915 --> 55:55.551
I'm sure there's something
we can do-- there has to be.
<i>Oh, all right.</i>

55:55.553 --> 55:58.620
I'll meet them. When?

55:59.756 --> 56:01.857
Good.

56:02.992 --> 56:03.759
Well, now, um--

56:03.761 --> 56:09.398
the actual legal side of
the company is really more in
the hands of my brother-in-law.

56:09.400 --> 56:13.969
So what I think we should do
is-is-is I'll consult with him.

56:13.971 --> 56:19.742
No.
You know what might be
a better idea?

56:19.744 --> 56:22.010
I could introduce you to him.

56:22.012 --> 56:24.546
You could come to our house
for dinner one night.

56:24.548 --> 56:30.886
I would love you to meet
my sister too.
Well, that sounds fine.

56:31.020 --> 56:34.790
You mean
you'll come for dinner?
Sure. Why not?

56:34.792 --> 56:38.160
I mean,
we live in New Rochelle.

56:38.162 --> 56:40.796
Well, that's okay.

56:40.798 --> 56:44.633
[ Chuckles ]

56:46.603 --> 56:49.037
[ Continues Laughing ]

56:51.508 --> 56:53.776
They're not gonna
believe this.

56:53.778 --> 56:57.780
[ Continues Laughing ]

56:58.915 --> 57:01.517
[ Clock Chiming ]

57:10.493 --> 57:15.664
Where is the young lady?
Well, obviously she isn't here.

57:19.102 --> 57:20.736
Let's eat.

57:20.738 --> 57:24.706
Oh, please, please,
let's just eat.

57:32.649 --> 57:35.684
Aren't we going to get
any kind of explanation?

57:35.686 --> 57:38.587
Well, I really don't want
to talk about it.

57:38.589 --> 57:42.057
[ Chuckles ]
I'm afraid that's
not good enough.

57:42.059 --> 57:46.795
I don't want to talk about it,
and if anyone asks me
another question,

57:46.797 --> 57:49.698
I am just going to leave.

57:50.500 --> 57:53.802
I don't understand.
You create this mystery.

57:53.804 --> 57:57.840
You don't tell us
who this young lady is.

57:57.842 --> 58:02.911
You build up everyone's
expectations. It's very...

58:02.913 --> 58:06.048
[ Sighs ]
disappointing.

58:06.050 --> 58:09.218
Well, I'm disappointed,
too, sir, you know.

58:09.220 --> 58:12.654
Did you ever think of that?
I'm disappointed too.

58:12.656 --> 58:16.692
Why don't you ring
for the soup, dear?

58:23.099 --> 58:25.601
! Soup.

58:35.211 --> 58:36.879
Yes.

58:36.881 --> 58:39.648
<i>[ Door Chimes Ring ]</i>

58:41.985 --> 58:44.286
I'll get it.

58:57.300 --> 58:59.968
Dear, Mr. Walker is
here to see Sarah.

58:59.970 --> 59:05.274
I told him he could
wait in the drawing room
while I go up and speak to her.

59:08.611 --> 59:12.648
Who's that?
The baby's father.

59:12.982 --> 59:14.283
Or so <i>he</i> says.

59:14.285 --> 59:18.587
Would you mind
bringing her these?
There's a little note on there.

59:18.589 --> 59:23.325
Oh, they're so beautiful.
I'll be right back.

59:31.935 --> 59:36.838
<i>♪ [ Piano ]</i>

59:36.840 --> 59:39.708
<i>Excuse me.</i>

59:42.979 --> 59:45.714
Your piano's
badly in need of a tuning.

59:45.716 --> 59:49.017
You ought to take better care
of an instrument like this.

59:49.019 --> 59:52.354
Would you mind
closing the piano?

59:55.191 --> 59:58.093
Sit down, Mr. Walker.

59:59.028 --> 01:00:11.373
There are a few things
I'd like to ask you.

01:00:14.344 --> 01:00:18.780
Sarah. Sarah,
just say hello to him.

01:00:18.782 --> 01:00:21.717
Nothing can happen to you.
You're safe here.

01:00:21.719 --> 01:00:25.387
There can't be any harm
in just talking to him.

01:00:25.389 --> 01:00:27.356
Oh, yes, it is.
Yes, it is.

01:00:27.358 --> 01:00:32.995
Why?
He say one thing,
and then he say another thing.

01:00:32.997 --> 01:00:35.697
And he make it
all sound so good.

01:00:35.699 --> 01:00:41.103
It ain't nothin'
but talk, ma'am.
It ain't nothin' but talk.

01:00:41.105 --> 01:00:43.105
I can marry Sarah,

01:00:43.107 --> 01:00:46.842
and I will,
soon as she'll have me.

01:00:46.844 --> 01:00:49.311
<i>I couldn't before,</i>
<i>and now I can.</i>

01:00:49.313 --> 01:00:51.179
That's very fancy reasoning,
Mr. Walker,

01:00:51.181 --> 01:00:54.683
but what it comes down to is
that you behaved abominably.

01:00:54.685 --> 01:00:59.421
[ Sighs ] I wasn't living
any kind of life I could ask
a woman to share with me--

01:00:59.423 --> 01:01:03.358
<i>playing in beer halls,</i>
<i>moving-picture houses.</i>

01:01:03.360 --> 01:01:06.962
Some of those places
aren't even safe
for a man to be in.

01:01:06.964 --> 01:01:09.064
So you just abandoned her?

01:01:09.066 --> 01:01:13.035
<i>That's how you handle</i>
<i>your responsibilities?</i>

01:01:13.037 --> 01:01:18.306
Uh, what kind
of music do you play?

01:01:19.976 --> 01:01:24.446
Anything they ask me to,
and then I play ragtime.

01:01:24.781 --> 01:01:30.052
Well, we have some music here.
Could you give us a tune?

01:01:31.087 --> 01:01:34.056
Uh, maybe some other time.

01:01:34.223 --> 01:01:36.958
I think what Mr. Walker's
trying to say...

01:01:36.960 --> 01:01:39.194
is that he
doesn't read music.

01:01:39.196 --> 01:01:41.730
Am I right, Mr. Walker?

01:01:41.732 --> 01:01:45.734
I read music so good,
white folks think I'm fakin' it.

01:01:45.736 --> 01:01:47.903
[ Laughing ]

01:01:59.982 --> 01:02:03.218
<i>♪ [ Classical ]</i>

01:02:27.477 --> 01:02:31.480
♪ [ Slow Ragtime ]

01:03:24.467 --> 01:03:27.302
[ Sobbing ]

01:03:31.974 --> 01:03:33.308
[ Footsteps ]

01:03:33.310 --> 01:03:37.145
Oh, no, no.
Please, please,
please don't get up.

01:03:37.147 --> 01:03:40.215
Are you all free
next weekend?

01:03:40.550 --> 01:03:43.819
I'd like you to be
at the wedding.

01:03:43.821 --> 01:03:46.054
What?

01:03:46.823 --> 01:03:48.523
Sarah's accepted my hand.

01:03:48.525 --> 01:03:54.429
After all you've done for her,
it wouldn't be much of a wedding
if you all weren't there.

01:03:54.431 --> 01:03:57.566
<i>Now, I hope you'll accept.</i>

01:03:59.101 --> 01:04:00.969
<i>No, no, no,</i>
<i>don't bother yourself now.</i>

01:04:00.971 --> 01:04:06.141
I have to go now 'cause
it's a long drive back.
I'll see you next Sunday.

01:04:06.143 --> 01:04:09.978
<i>I'll see you.</i>
<i>[ Yells ]</i>

01:04:14.917 --> 01:04:17.619
- [ Shouts ]
- [ Laughs ]

01:04:18.421 --> 01:04:21.623
[ Laughing ]

01:04:30.499 --> 01:04:33.101
[ Engine Starts ]

01:04:36.205 --> 01:04:40.108
♪ [ Piano ]
[ Man ]
And ladylike.

01:04:41.577 --> 01:04:45.046
That's it.
And around we go.

01:04:45.048 --> 01:04:47.482
And around.

01:04:47.984 --> 01:04:51.953
Beautiful.
Now the horsey.

01:04:52.088 --> 01:04:56.191
Now another horsey.
And a peekaboo.

01:05:00.563 --> 01:05:02.597
There we are.

01:05:02.599 --> 01:05:04.065
Evelyn?

01:05:04.067 --> 01:05:06.067
<i>Evelyn--</i>
<i>Quiet, please! Quiet!</i>

01:05:06.069 --> 01:05:08.970
Evelyn, I have something
very important to say to you.

01:05:08.972 --> 01:05:13.108
<i>Please.</i>
<i>You know what this guy</i>
<i>is talking about?</i>

01:05:13.110 --> 01:05:15.043
Okay, five minutes.

01:05:15.045 --> 01:05:18.413
Oh, uh, I, I, I--
Oh, I--

01:05:20.416 --> 01:05:24.119
You moved.
You didn't tell me
where you were going.

01:05:24.121 --> 01:05:25.987
I was evicted.
It wasn't my fault.

01:05:25.989 --> 01:05:29.357
You said you'd come to dinner.
How was I supposed to find you?

01:05:29.359 --> 01:05:32.661
Did I do something wrong?
What did I do wrong?
Just tell me.

01:05:32.663 --> 01:05:35.630
Not now, sweetheart.
Yes, now!

01:05:35.632 --> 01:05:38.566
I want an explanation.

01:05:38.568 --> 01:05:41.503
W-- I can't think
about this right now.

01:05:41.505 --> 01:05:45.106
I've got a lot
on my mind.
Well, so do I.

01:05:45.108 --> 01:05:48.677
I'm trying to do well
in the firm.
I try so hard.

01:05:48.679 --> 01:05:52.948
And sometimes everything
seems to be going fine,
and then I don't know.

01:05:52.950 --> 01:05:56.551
I don't know
what's wrong with me.
It just all falls apart.

01:05:56.553 --> 01:05:59.554
I can't-- I can't even
walk down the street...

01:05:59.556 --> 01:06:05.560
without-- without being
afraid that somebody's
gonna talk to me.

01:06:05.562 --> 01:06:07.095
I need you to be with me.

01:06:07.097 --> 01:06:11.733
<i>You have to, Evelyn.</i>
<i>Okay, darling, that's it.</i>
<i>Back to work.</i>

01:06:12.668 --> 01:06:15.537
I've gotta go.
No.

01:06:15.539 --> 01:06:16.571
Yes.
No.

01:06:16.573 --> 01:06:18.473
That's not very nice, mister.
The lady wants to go.

01:06:18.475 --> 01:06:22.243
You don't know what kind
of pressure I've been under.
I can't do anything about that.

01:06:22.245 --> 01:06:25.113
Yes, you can!
I just want to know
where you live.

01:06:25.115 --> 01:06:27.716
Just tell me
where you live!
Let go of my arm!

01:06:27.718 --> 01:06:30.618
<i>God-- Goddamn it!</i>
<i>I'm not talking to you!</i>

01:06:30.620 --> 01:06:33.054
<i>This is none of</i>
<i>your goddamn business!</i>

01:06:33.056 --> 01:06:38.593
This is none of your
business! None of your--
Take it easy.

01:06:43.099 --> 01:06:46.101
[ Bell Ringing ]

01:06:53.342 --> 01:06:56.244
[ Bell Ringing ]

01:07:11.460 --> 01:07:15.130
[ Shouting ]

01:07:32.448 --> 01:07:35.183
- Excuse me.
- Hmm?

01:07:35.185 --> 01:07:39.054
Could you tell me how long
that'll be standing there?

01:07:39.056 --> 01:07:43.458
- How's that?
- I have to pass by.

01:07:44.260 --> 01:07:49.297
Oh, well, uh,
you got your toll?

01:07:50.199 --> 01:07:53.201
Toll? There's no toll
on this road.

01:07:53.203 --> 01:07:58.339
Sure, there is.
This here's a private toll road.
Ain't it, fellas?

01:07:58.341 --> 01:08:01.242
<i>[ Men Agreeing ]</i>

01:08:01.410 --> 01:08:06.247
I've used this road
several times, and I've
never had to pay a toll.

01:08:06.249 --> 01:08:10.718
Well, somebody must've
been sleeping on duty.

01:08:10.720 --> 01:08:13.388
<i>[ Men Chuckling ]</i>

01:08:17.158 --> 01:08:21.196
All right.
How much is the toll?

01:08:21.796 --> 01:08:25.433
[ Clears Throat ]
Willie?

01:08:26.301 --> 01:08:28.837
Hey, uh, Willie!

01:08:28.839 --> 01:08:32.372
How much is the toll today?

01:08:39.215 --> 01:08:42.216
What's that--
A Model T?

01:08:42.618 --> 01:08:47.388
- Who you driving it for?
- It's my automobile.

01:08:47.390 --> 01:08:50.358
I own it.
<i>[ Man Laughing ]</i>

01:08:50.359 --> 01:08:54.295
My God.
Don't that beat all?

01:08:54.296 --> 01:08:57.765
<i>[ Man Laughing ]</i>
<i>How much is the toll?</i>

01:08:57.767 --> 01:08:59.901
Oh, the toll.

01:08:59.903 --> 01:09:01.469
Uh-- Let's see.

01:09:01.470 --> 01:09:05.240
Today is Sunday.
Twenty-five dollars.

01:09:05.242 --> 01:09:06.674
<i>[ Men Laughing ]</i>

01:09:06.676 --> 01:09:11.712
We're trying
to raise a little cash for
a fire wagon with an engine.

01:09:11.715 --> 01:09:15.649
<i>Hell, we want to drive</i>
<i>to our fires in style,</i>

01:09:15.652 --> 01:09:19.821
just like you drive
to your cathouses.

01:09:19.823 --> 01:09:22.689
[ Men Laughing ]

01:09:22.692 --> 01:09:25.527
[ Engine Stops ]

01:09:37.473 --> 01:09:39.707
[ Horn Honks ]

01:09:39.709 --> 01:09:41.576
[ Man Laughs ]

01:09:41.578 --> 01:09:44.812
[ Horn Honking ]

01:09:52.488 --> 01:09:55.490
[ Chattering ]

01:09:55.492 --> 01:09:58.593
Has he got the nigger
with him?

01:09:58.595 --> 01:10:00.962
[ Man Giggling ]

01:10:00.964 --> 01:10:02.497
Hey, Frankie.

01:10:02.499 --> 01:10:07.302
What the hell
are you doing here?
Where is my car?

01:10:08.537 --> 01:10:10.872
Is that it?

01:10:14.877 --> 01:10:19.981
<i>All right.</i>
<i>Let's just forget about it.</i>
<i>Go get your car.</i>

01:10:19.983 --> 01:10:21.916
[ Sighs ]
Thank you.

01:10:21.918 --> 01:10:25.320
It's all right.
[ Man ]
Deal the cards. Let's go.

01:10:25.322 --> 01:10:28.323
How many?
I call. Let's go.

01:10:28.325 --> 01:10:31.259
Come on.
[ Men Chattering ]

01:10:31.261 --> 01:10:34.862
Jesus, Mary and Joseph.
Ain't you got enough fires
to keep you busy, Willie?

01:10:34.864 --> 01:10:40.235
What the hell's gotten into you?
Nobody around here can take
a joke anymore.

01:10:40.237 --> 01:10:41.903
Officer!

01:10:41.905 --> 01:10:45.707
Could you please come here
and look at this?

01:11:05.694 --> 01:11:08.563
Whew! That smells.
I want this cleaned up.

01:11:08.565 --> 01:11:11.699
[ Fly Buzzing ]
[ Willie ]
Oh, I don't blame ya.

01:11:11.701 --> 01:11:13.835
It's a hell of a shame.
[ Horse Whinnying ]

01:11:13.837 --> 01:11:17.805
[ Chuckles ]
Brand-new car like that.
I want it cleaned up.

01:11:17.807 --> 01:11:21.876
Go ahead. Clean it up.
Can it, Willie.
Nobody's laughing.

01:11:21.878 --> 01:11:25.280
Now, what the hell do you boys
think you're up to?

01:11:25.282 --> 01:11:27.815
I'll tell you exactly
what happened, Frankie.

01:11:27.817 --> 01:11:30.618
This here fancy nigger parked
in front of the firehouse.

01:11:30.620 --> 01:11:33.021
Now, if you don't think
that's a serious business,

01:11:33.023 --> 01:11:36.624
tell me about it
when your house is burning,
we can't get the pump out,

01:11:36.626 --> 01:11:39.360
and the road's all blocked
because of a nigger's car.

01:11:39.362 --> 01:11:43.064
I had no intention
of stopping in front
of the firehouse,

01:11:43.066 --> 01:11:44.632
but my way was blocked.

01:11:44.634 --> 01:11:49.404
I don't know why you did this.
I never caused you any harm.

01:11:49.571 --> 01:11:51.706
You blocked access
to an emergency service,

01:11:51.708 --> 01:11:55.877
and I got witnesses here
to prove it!
You're lying.

01:11:55.879 --> 01:11:58.946
Willie, no!
Don't you say
that to me!

01:11:58.948 --> 01:12:02.383
- Nigger!
- Come on, come on, come on.

01:12:02.385 --> 01:12:04.952
Over here.
Right there.

01:12:06.088 --> 01:12:09.090
<i>[ Horse Whinnying ]</i>
<i>[ Sighs ]</i>
<i>Look.</i>

01:12:09.092 --> 01:12:11.092
[ Sighs ]
There ain't
no real damage done.

01:12:11.094 --> 01:12:17.532
Just... scoop the shit off,
take your automobile,
and get along outta here.

01:12:17.534 --> 01:12:20.702
<i>What do you say?</i>

01:12:21.070 --> 01:12:24.405
I'm not goin' nowhere
until my car is cleaned.

01:12:24.407 --> 01:12:28.576
I don't want no trouble.
Just do as I say.

01:12:28.744 --> 01:12:30.945
You know I'm telling
the truth.
Just get in your car--

01:12:30.947 --> 01:12:35.116
Why are you letting
these men intimidate you?
Nobody's intimidating me!

01:12:35.118 --> 01:12:39.654
You just don't know what you're
getting into, and I'm trying
to keep your nose clean.

01:12:39.656 --> 01:12:43.624
Would you be a good boy
and just get along!

01:12:43.626 --> 01:12:45.693
I want my car cleaned.

01:12:45.695 --> 01:12:47.962
Clean it then, damn you!
Clean it and go!

01:12:47.964 --> 01:12:49.897
I want the man who did it
to clean it!

01:12:49.899 --> 01:12:53.101
[ Frankie ]
All right. All right.
Let me put it this way.

01:12:53.103 --> 01:12:57.071
I can arrest you
for blocking
a public service exit,

01:12:57.073 --> 01:12:58.473
for creating
a public nuisance...

01:12:58.475 --> 01:13:01.542
and about ten other things
that I ain't gonna bother
to mention.

01:13:01.544 --> 01:13:04.746
Now, am I making
myself clear?

01:13:05.514 --> 01:13:07.615
Yes.
Good.

01:13:07.617 --> 01:13:08.816
Officer,

01:13:08.818 --> 01:13:11.853
I still want
my car cleaned.
Oh, for Christ's sakes.

01:13:11.855 --> 01:13:17.024
Ain't you got
any sense in your head?
I'm trying to help you.

01:13:19.695 --> 01:13:22.630
You leave me no choice.

01:13:24.400 --> 01:13:26.768
I'm sorry.

01:13:27.836 --> 01:13:30.938
You're under arrest.

01:13:35.711 --> 01:13:38.012
[ Ringing ]

01:13:38.014 --> 01:13:40.715
It's all right.
Yes, sir.

01:13:40.717 --> 01:13:42.884
Yes?

01:13:46.989 --> 01:13:49.590
Yes.

01:13:50.058 --> 01:13:53.594
I see.
I'll be right down.

01:14:02.471 --> 01:14:04.639
Better be getting yourself
some new help.

01:14:04.641 --> 01:14:09.177
Once a nigger goes wrong,
there's no putting him right.

01:14:09.179 --> 01:14:12.680
[ Typewriter Keys Clacking ]

01:14:21.223 --> 01:14:23.825
Thank you, sir.

01:14:34.703 --> 01:14:37.505
Whoa! Whoa!

01:14:42.578 --> 01:14:46.781
Well, what happened?
You said there wasn't
any physical damage done.

01:14:46.783 --> 01:14:50.017
There wasn't
when I was arrested.

01:14:50.019 --> 01:14:51.085
[ Sighs ]

01:14:51.087 --> 01:14:56.624
This is what I was saying.
You should have just
cleaned it up to begin with.

01:14:56.626 --> 01:14:59.227
Now look what's happened.

01:14:59.661 --> 01:15:02.029
Well, the damage
isn't that bad.

01:15:02.031 --> 01:15:05.600
<i>It shouldn't take much</i>
<i>to put it right.</i>

01:15:05.602 --> 01:15:09.036
Please, if you would be
kind enough to tell Sarah
what happened,

01:15:09.038 --> 01:15:10.638
but tell her not to worry.

01:15:10.640 --> 01:15:15.977
And tell her that I'll be
talking with her soon.

01:15:15.979 --> 01:15:18.746
Hey, wait a minute!
Stop!

01:15:20.549 --> 01:15:22.783
I'm talking to you.

01:15:22.785 --> 01:15:23.251
Yes?

01:15:23.253 --> 01:15:27.855
Well, you can't just leave
this out here all night,
you know.

01:15:27.857 --> 01:15:30.157
You don't know
who's gonna come along.

01:15:30.159 --> 01:15:33.728
It's a little late
for that kind of thinking,
and I have to work tonight.

01:15:33.730 --> 01:15:40.034
Good afternoon.
That is not a very helpful
attitude, Mr. Walker.

01:15:40.202 --> 01:15:42.003
We're trying to help you,
you know.

01:15:42.005 --> 01:15:48.543
I've spent a lot of time trying
to get this business cleared up,
not to mention money.

01:15:48.677 --> 01:15:53.881
I think we should
work out exactly what
we're going to do now.

01:15:53.883 --> 01:15:57.084
I haven't decided yet.

01:15:57.086 --> 01:15:59.787
Good afternoon.

01:16:06.562 --> 01:16:10.231
Well, what's your
financial situation like?

01:16:11.833 --> 01:16:13.701
[ Sighs ]
I have a little laid by.

01:16:13.703 --> 01:16:17.171
I planned to use it
on my wedding, but I guess
it'll have to wait.

01:16:17.173 --> 01:16:22.209
Mm. Mr. Walker, let me
give you some advice.

01:16:22.711 --> 01:16:24.078
You spend the money
on your wedding.

01:16:24.080 --> 01:16:28.583
Build yourself a home
and a family where you
can find some comfort.

01:16:28.585 --> 01:16:34.088
And just forget
that some damn white man
caused you offense.

01:16:35.591 --> 01:16:37.892
And that's your advice?

01:16:37.894 --> 01:16:41.729
That's my advice, and I pray
you take it to heart.

01:16:41.731 --> 01:16:44.832
"Just forget it"?
Is that it?

01:16:45.734 --> 01:16:47.768
I've spent my whole life
forgetting.

01:16:47.770 --> 01:16:51.339
You're a young man.
You better start learning now.

01:16:51.341 --> 01:16:55.743
Learning what--
how to be a nigger?

01:17:00.015 --> 01:17:02.683
Mr. Walker,
I'll thank you to leave.

01:17:02.685 --> 01:17:05.987
I have some charity cases
you know nothing of.

01:17:05.989 --> 01:17:08.990
<i>I got clients with</i>
<i>real problems--</i>

01:17:08.992 --> 01:17:11.959
<i>starvation, illness,</i>

01:17:11.961 --> 01:17:13.227
dispossession.

01:17:13.229 --> 01:17:17.231
Yes, I want justice
for our people.
Yes, I do.

01:17:17.233 --> 01:17:19.634
I want it so bad,
I can taste it.

01:17:19.636 --> 01:17:24.972
If you think I'll go
to Westchester County pleading
the behalf of a colored man...

01:17:24.974 --> 01:17:27.642
that somebody dirtied
his fancy car,

01:17:27.644 --> 01:17:30.945
you are very much
mistaken.

01:17:30.947 --> 01:17:34.749
Now, please,
you take this...

01:17:34.751 --> 01:17:37.151
and leave my office.

01:17:40.122 --> 01:17:44.759
I'm afraid you can't file
a complaint against
a volunteer fireman.

01:17:44.761 --> 01:17:49.263
Why not?
Because they're not
an employee of the city.

01:17:49.265 --> 01:17:52.933
We have no jurisdiction
over them.

01:17:52.935 --> 01:17:56.337
Well, then whose jurisdiction
are they under?

01:17:57.105 --> 01:18:00.875
Well, they got it wrong.
You're gonna have to go back
to the police department...

01:18:00.877 --> 01:18:04.979
and tell them I said you should
file your complaint with them.

01:18:04.981 --> 01:18:06.681
That's instructions
from the county clerk.

01:18:06.683 --> 01:18:10.685
I don't care what they told you
at the county clerk's office.

01:18:10.687 --> 01:18:13.254
Then tell me what
I'm supposed to do.

01:18:13.256 --> 01:18:16.924
Just explain to me exactly
how I should go about it.

01:18:16.926 --> 01:18:19.326
The first thing you can do
is go to the county clerk...

01:18:19.328 --> 01:18:24.465
and tell the son of a bitch
not to send you back here!

01:18:25.701 --> 01:18:27.001
Now-- now, listen.

01:18:27.003 --> 01:18:31.839
All I'm saying is
that I want you
to talk to Mr. Walker.

01:18:31.841 --> 01:18:35.309
[ Sniffles ]
I did.

01:18:35.877 --> 01:18:41.015
He got hisself all crazy
over this thing.

01:18:41.983 --> 01:18:44.985
He ain't got no time
for me now.

01:18:44.987 --> 01:18:49.223
[ Sobbing ]
But, uh, that's
what I'm saying.

01:18:49.225 --> 01:18:52.993
And we can't keep
you here forever.

01:18:52.995 --> 01:18:57.965
I do my work around the house,
if that's what you want.

01:18:57.967 --> 01:18:59.834
No, I only want one thing.

01:18:59.836 --> 01:19:03.003
I want you to make
Mr. Walker understand...

01:19:03.005 --> 01:19:06.373
<i>that there's absolutely</i>
<i>no legal means...</i>

01:19:06.375 --> 01:19:08.309
<i>for redressing this thing.</i>

01:19:08.311 --> 01:19:12.146
Why are you telling
her that? That's not
what the lawyers said.

01:19:12.148 --> 01:19:14.482
Will you let me
handle this, please?

01:19:14.484 --> 01:19:16.751
They said it would take
a lot of time and money,

01:19:16.753 --> 01:19:19.286
but they <i>never</i> said
that there was no chance.

01:19:19.288 --> 01:19:21.922
I am trying to present
this situation...

01:19:21.924 --> 01:19:24.458
in a way she's capable
of understanding!

01:19:24.460 --> 01:19:26.527
But you're lying to her.
Get out!

01:19:26.529 --> 01:19:30.164
I told you to get
out of here!

01:19:40.408 --> 01:19:44.278
Sarah? Sarah,
now, listen to me.

01:19:44.280 --> 01:19:44.979
Listen.

01:19:44.981 --> 01:19:49.283
All right. Now, you can tell
Mr. Walker that if he'll
just marry you...

01:19:49.285 --> 01:19:51.418
without any more
of this nonsense,

01:19:51.420 --> 01:19:55.389
I'll pay to have
his automobile repaired.

01:19:56.324 --> 01:19:58.025
That ain't gonna do
no good...

01:19:58.027 --> 01:20:02.830
[ Panting ]
'cause he say it got
to be the firemen.

01:20:02.832 --> 01:20:07.902
Oh, for pity's sake.
What difference does it make?

01:20:08.036 --> 01:20:11.806
I told him--
I told him I'd clean it.

01:20:11.808 --> 01:20:15.142
I'd clean it.
But he said no.

01:20:15.144 --> 01:20:17.545
Well, if he's not willing
to see reason,

01:20:17.547 --> 01:20:23.017
then it's your responsibility
to do something about it.

01:20:23.019 --> 01:20:25.419
Do you understand?

01:20:25.421 --> 01:20:26.954
Uh-huh.

01:20:26.956 --> 01:20:30.191
It's your
responsibility now.

01:20:34.963 --> 01:20:38.065
[ Baby Crying ]

01:20:45.340 --> 01:20:48.442
<i>[ Crying Continues ]</i>

01:20:51.413 --> 01:20:53.881
Shh.
[ Coughing ]

01:20:53.883 --> 01:20:55.449
Oh, baby.

01:20:55.451 --> 01:20:57.952
Where's your mommy, huh?

01:20:57.954 --> 01:21:00.154
Where'd your mommy go?

01:21:00.156 --> 01:21:02.556
[ Crickets Chirping ]

01:21:10.298 --> 01:21:13.934
♪ [ Band Playing ]

01:21:13.936 --> 01:21:20.641
♪

01:21:20.643 --> 01:21:22.943
[ Crowd Shouting ]

01:21:22.945 --> 01:21:25.946
[ Crowd Cheering ]

01:21:32.287 --> 01:21:34.989
[ Cheering ]

01:21:50.939 --> 01:21:54.275
[ Firecrackers
Continue Popping ]

01:22:00.248 --> 01:22:01.415
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

01:22:01.417 --> 01:22:06.987
<i>the vice president</i>
<i>of the United States,</i>
<i>Charles Fairbanks.</i>

01:22:06.989 --> 01:22:10.557
[ All Cheering ]

01:22:16.298 --> 01:22:20.034
A few days ago,
I went to the president...

01:22:20.036 --> 01:22:21.502
and I said to him,
"Colonel,

01:22:21.504 --> 01:22:27.308
"I'm about to visit the great
northeast of this country
and meet the people.

01:22:27.310 --> 01:22:30.344
Is there anything
you want me to tell them?"

01:22:30.346 --> 01:22:32.246
You know what he said?
He said to me,

01:22:32.248 --> 01:22:38.452
"Charles, just tell them
that the door to my office
is always open."

01:22:38.454 --> 01:22:42.189
<i>[ Cheering, Applause ]</i>

01:22:42.457 --> 01:22:47.061
You good people of
White Plains voted for us
in the last election.

01:22:47.063 --> 01:22:49.196
You knew what we stood for then.

01:22:49.198 --> 01:22:53.133
We haven't changed,
and we hope you haven't either.

01:22:53.135 --> 01:22:57.604
Good health, enterprise,
self-reliance.

01:22:57.606 --> 01:23:02.209
I'm talking about the man who
wants to get out there and do--

01:23:02.211 --> 01:23:05.713
Stay back, please,
Stay back.
Mr. President!

01:23:05.715 --> 01:23:07.648
...who sees an opportunity...

01:23:07.650 --> 01:23:10.985
and grabs it by the tail.
Mr. President! Mr. Pres--

01:23:10.987 --> 01:23:13.687
- Ow!
- You gotta help
Coalhouse Walker!

01:23:13.689 --> 01:23:16.290
- [ Screaming ]
- <i>[ Fairbanks Continues ]</i>

01:23:16.292 --> 01:23:19.426
♪ [ Band Playing ]
[ Blows Landing ]

01:23:19.428 --> 01:23:22.396
[ Cheering ]

01:23:22.398 --> 01:23:26.600
Make way.
Coming through.
Coming through.

01:23:27.502 --> 01:23:32.773
I'm sorry. Make way.
Make way. Make way.

01:23:34.009 --> 01:23:37.478
Her sternum was crushed,
and she's sustained very
severe internal injuries.

01:23:37.480 --> 01:23:44.651
I'm afraid you'll have to keep
her dry and warm, and pray that
she doesn't develop pneumonia.

01:23:46.554 --> 01:23:50.257
Uh, this is her husband.

01:24:15.250 --> 01:24:17.785
Shh.

01:24:18.286 --> 01:24:21.522
The president knows
who you are now.

01:24:21.524 --> 01:24:25.793
I said your whole name
before they got to me.

01:24:25.795 --> 01:24:28.762
That's good.
Shh, shh, shh.

01:24:28.764 --> 01:24:31.365
Don't talk now.

01:24:31.499 --> 01:24:36.103
<i>But I didn't get a chance</i>
<i>to tell him what you want.</i>

01:24:36.105 --> 01:24:41.442
So you gotta
write him a letter.
I will.

01:24:44.446 --> 01:24:47.347
I spoke with a minister
yesterday.

01:24:47.515 --> 01:24:54.721
He said he would marry us,
even with the baby and all.
Oh! [ Laughs ]

01:24:55.123 --> 01:24:59.293
Now, we're gonna have
the whole Clef Club Orchestra.
<i>Oh!</i>

01:24:59.295 --> 01:25:01.795
They're gonna play for us.
And a choir.

01:25:01.797 --> 01:25:07.101
[ Laughs ]
And it's gonna be
in a big, big church...

01:25:07.103 --> 01:25:09.803
like you never seen before.

01:25:09.805 --> 01:25:11.839
Ooh!

01:25:11.841 --> 01:25:14.141
Which one?

01:25:14.143 --> 01:25:16.743
Shh!

01:25:16.745 --> 01:25:18.512
You just rest.

01:25:18.514 --> 01:25:22.316
♪ [ Band Playing Hymn ]

01:25:23.651 --> 01:25:27.387
♪ [ Band Continues ]

01:26:13.768 --> 01:26:16.170
Ace.
Ah. That's two bits.

01:26:16.172 --> 01:26:18.639
Jesus Christ.
You lucky bastard.

01:26:18.641 --> 01:26:21.909
[ Irish Brogue ]
It's the luck of
the Irish, me boy.

01:26:21.911 --> 01:26:24.511
[ Laughs ]
[ Phone Ringing ]

01:26:24.513 --> 01:26:27.548
Three.
Answer the phone.

01:26:27.682 --> 01:26:31.952
Hold those cards.
Nobody bets.
[ Ringing Continues ]

01:26:32.720 --> 01:26:34.755
Emerald Isle Firehouse.

01:26:34.757 --> 01:26:37.691
[ Crickets Chirping ]

01:26:38.359 --> 01:26:41.495
Let's go, guys. This is it.
Come on. Let's go.

01:26:41.497 --> 01:26:44.398
Come on.
Hey, kid, let's go.
Come on. Let's go.

01:26:44.400 --> 01:26:48.802
Come on. Let's go.
Move! Move! Come on.
Down the pole.

01:26:48.804 --> 01:26:52.406
<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>

01:26:52.408 --> 01:26:54.841
[ Gunshots ]

01:26:55.944 --> 01:26:58.712
[ Horses Whinnying ]

01:27:00.248 --> 01:27:04.218
[ Gunshots ]
[ Dogs Barking
In The Distance ]

01:27:04.220 --> 01:27:07.721
Where's Conklin?

01:27:09.457 --> 01:27:11.258
Which one of you
is Conklin?
Don't shoot me!

01:27:11.260 --> 01:27:15.229
Tell me which of you is Conklin.
I don't know!
[ Mutters ]

01:27:15.231 --> 01:27:17.264
Where's Conklin?

01:27:17.266 --> 01:27:19.299
Where's Conklin?
No! No!

01:27:19.301 --> 01:27:23.770
Damn it, where's Conklin?
He's not here!

01:27:24.272 --> 01:27:25.939
Let's go! Let's go!

01:27:25.941 --> 01:27:29.343
[ Dogs Barking
In The Distance ]

01:27:30.845 --> 01:27:33.313
<i>"I want the infamous...</i>

01:27:33.315 --> 01:27:37.651
"fire chief, William Conklin,
turned over to my justice.

01:27:37.653 --> 01:27:42.856
"I want my automobile
returned to me
in its original condition.

01:27:42.858 --> 01:27:45.459
<i>"When you are ready</i>
<i> to meet my demands,</i>

01:27:45.461 --> 01:27:48.295
<i>"please make it known</i>
<i> in the newspapers.</i>

01:27:48.297 --> 01:27:50.931
<i>"If you refuse me,</i>
<i> I shall continue...</i>

01:27:50.933 --> 01:27:54.468
"to burn firehouses
and kill firemen...

01:27:55.536 --> 01:27:58.538
<i>"until I have</i>
<i> satisfaction.</i>

01:28:00.041 --> 01:28:02.643
Coalhouse Walker, Jr."

01:28:02.645 --> 01:28:04.911
That's that crazy nigger
with the car!

01:28:04.913 --> 01:28:08.015
So, you know
all about him, do ya?

01:28:08.017 --> 01:28:12.352
- Sure as hell, I do.
- What do you know exactly,
Mr. Conklin?

01:28:12.354 --> 01:28:15.555
Well, you had him all arrested
for parking his car illegal.

01:28:15.557 --> 01:28:19.826
You had him behind bars
where he belongs.
Now he's running around loose.

01:28:19.828 --> 01:28:23.530
Whose fault
do you suppose that is?
Not mine, I'll tell you that.

01:28:23.532 --> 01:28:27.534
Well, Willie, we have
a little problem on our hands.

01:28:27.536 --> 01:28:29.770
Well, you got a problem, do ya?
[ Chuckles ]

01:28:29.772 --> 01:28:34.408
How do you suppose I feel?
Those were my men he killed!

01:28:34.410 --> 01:28:37.544
We heard something
about excrement in his car.

01:28:37.546 --> 01:28:40.714
So? What are you messin'
around with me for?

01:28:40.716 --> 01:28:43.383
We're just trying
to piece it all together.

01:28:43.385 --> 01:28:46.320
Go out and arrest every nigger
in the neighborhood.

01:28:46.322 --> 01:28:48.622
One of them's bound
to know where he is.

01:28:48.624 --> 01:28:50.991
They all know everything
about each other, right?

01:28:50.993 --> 01:28:54.995
That's a grand piece
of thinking, Willie.

01:28:54.997 --> 01:28:57.564
But, you see,

01:28:57.566 --> 01:29:01.568
we had a different
sort of plan in mind.

01:29:01.570 --> 01:29:06.807
What's that?
Offer to turn
you over to him.

01:29:06.809 --> 01:29:09.943
[ Scoffs ]
You're a funny man, Inspector.

01:29:09.945 --> 01:29:14.981
Well, Willie,
it's the easiest way
to find him, isn't it?

01:29:15.950 --> 01:29:19.453
And the cheapest,
don't you think?

01:29:19.987 --> 01:29:23.023
Hey, fellas, be serious,
will ya, huh?

01:29:23.025 --> 01:29:26.126
I ain't laughing, you see.

01:29:27.462 --> 01:29:30.864
<i>Aren't we all</i>
<i>in this together?</i>

01:29:32.100 --> 01:29:34.067
Right?

01:29:34.069 --> 01:29:37.104
Aren't we all
in this together?

01:29:40.875 --> 01:29:42.042
[ Hoofbeats ]

01:29:42.044 --> 01:29:47.547
- <i>Would you say he seemed</i>
<i>  fairly attached to the baby?</i>
<i>- Yes.</i>

01:29:47.549 --> 01:29:50.917
Do you think he'll try
to get the baby back?

01:29:50.919 --> 01:29:53.520
I don't know.

01:29:54.389 --> 01:29:56.957
I really don't know.

01:30:00.161 --> 01:30:03.997
Maybe we should post
a man here at the house.

01:30:04.832 --> 01:30:08.068
Just so there'll be someone
around who'll know what to do...

01:30:08.070 --> 01:30:12.005
in case he tries
to get in touch.

01:30:13.608 --> 01:30:15.609
Is that really necessary?

01:30:15.611 --> 01:30:17.677
It's for your
own protection too.

01:30:17.679 --> 01:30:22.416
You never know
with these people, if he
wants the baby badly enough.

01:30:22.583 --> 01:30:26.153
Well, maybe in that case
we could take the baby
to my cousin's house.

01:30:26.155 --> 01:30:32.459
No, ma'am, we prefer
that Mr. Walker knows
where the baby is.

01:30:32.461 --> 01:30:34.694
Oh.

01:30:34.696 --> 01:30:35.962
I see.

01:30:35.964 --> 01:30:39.065
It'd be better,
having someone here.

01:30:57.018 --> 01:30:58.485
Good evening, sir.
A table?

01:30:58.487 --> 01:31:01.822
I'm looking
for Coalhouse Walker.
He's a piano player.

01:31:01.824 --> 01:31:03.723
Sorry. He doesn't work
here anymore.

01:31:03.725 --> 01:31:06.893
Do you know where I could
get in touch with him?
It's important.

01:31:06.895 --> 01:31:09.996
I don't know where he is.
Sorry. He stopped working here.

01:31:09.998 --> 01:31:13.099
You don't have
any address--

01:31:14.135 --> 01:31:15.902
Yes, I see.
Why should you trust me?

01:31:15.904 --> 01:31:19.506
I'd like him to know
not to come near the house
in New Rochelle.

01:31:19.508 --> 01:31:24.711
It's not safe.
Sorry, Mr. Walker
doesn't work here anymore.

01:31:24.713 --> 01:31:25.812
I know, I know.

01:31:25.814 --> 01:31:29.716
But if you could give him
the message. It's important.

01:31:29.718 --> 01:31:32.118
Here's my card.

01:31:47.101 --> 01:31:49.836
[ Knock At Door ]

01:31:51.539 --> 01:31:53.740
Yes.

01:31:55.142 --> 01:31:57.777
May I come in?

01:32:10.057 --> 01:32:14.594
Can you explain this?
What is it?

01:32:15.196 --> 01:32:18.198
Someone in Harlem
gave it to the police.

01:32:18.200 --> 01:32:22.302
They said a young man was
looking for Coalhouse Walker.

01:32:24.305 --> 01:32:27.040
Yes, that was me.

01:32:28.075 --> 01:32:29.142
Why did you do that?

01:32:29.144 --> 01:32:33.780
I wanted to warn Mr. Walker that
our house was being watched.

01:32:34.815 --> 01:32:37.150
You damn fool.

01:32:37.919 --> 01:32:41.054
You don't seem to realize
how serious this situation is.

01:32:41.056 --> 01:32:47.060
- I think I do.
- Then why did you
try to help him?

01:32:49.597 --> 01:32:52.966
Are you planning
on doing it again?

01:32:52.968 --> 01:32:56.336
I hope not because
I gave the inspector
my word of honor...

01:32:56.338 --> 01:33:00.006
that you wouldn't do
anything foolish again.

01:33:00.008 --> 01:33:03.076
Now, can I trust you?

01:33:03.644 --> 01:33:08.048
- Yes, you can.
- Do I have your word on it?

01:33:08.050 --> 01:33:10.216
Yes.

01:33:13.588 --> 01:33:16.356
<i>[ Knock At Door ]</i>

01:33:17.758 --> 01:33:20.594
[ Knocking Continues ]

01:33:34.008 --> 01:33:36.610
Mr. Walker?

01:33:37.211 --> 01:33:38.144
Mr.-- Mr. Walker?

01:33:38.146 --> 01:33:42.716
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>What do you want with him?</i>
<i>I want to talk to him.</i>

01:33:43.351 --> 01:33:46.653
What do you want
to talk to him about?

01:33:46.655 --> 01:33:48.922
Who are you?
Don't worry
about who I am.

01:33:48.924 --> 01:33:52.792
<i>What do you want to</i>
<i>talk to Mr. Walker about?</i>
<i>Get him a chair.</i>

01:33:52.794 --> 01:33:55.729
Mr. Walker?
That's right.

01:33:58.699 --> 01:34:03.970
- Do I have to keep this on?
- I think you'd better.

01:34:04.905 --> 01:34:06.673
Okay.

01:34:06.675 --> 01:34:09.142
What can I do for you?

01:34:09.144 --> 01:34:11.745
Well, it's, uh,
just our house.

01:34:11.747 --> 01:34:15.915
You know your son
is still there.

01:34:16.417 --> 01:34:18.284
The... police...

01:34:18.286 --> 01:34:21.955
have a man
watching the place.

01:34:21.957 --> 01:34:25.125
Is that why you came here?

01:34:27.995 --> 01:34:30.230
No.

01:34:31.832 --> 01:34:34.100
Well?

01:34:34.102 --> 01:34:37.404
I design fireworks.
That's my job.

01:34:46.681 --> 01:34:49.049
I can make bombs.

01:34:53.954 --> 01:34:58.291
<i>Fireworks, bombs--</i>
<i>it's the same thing.</i>

01:35:34.361 --> 01:35:37.197
[ Glass Shattering ]

01:35:43.971 --> 01:35:47.073
Hey! Hey!
What's the idea?

01:35:51.345 --> 01:35:54.280
[ People Shouting ]

01:35:56.851 --> 01:35:58.918
[ All Shouting ]

01:35:58.920 --> 01:36:01.788
<i>[ Woman Shouting ]</i>

01:36:01.790 --> 01:36:04.858
[ Shouting ]

01:36:09.463 --> 01:36:12.232
[ Shouting Continues ]

01:36:12.234 --> 01:36:13.933
Get away from our house!

01:36:13.935 --> 01:36:17.771
This is a private residence.
You're all trespassing!

01:36:17.773 --> 01:36:21.274
Sir, let us see
the colored baby, okay?

01:36:21.276 --> 01:36:24.210
[ Men Shouting ]

01:36:24.212 --> 01:36:26.880
<i>!</i>
<i>Dear?</i>

01:36:27.481 --> 01:36:30.216
Thank God you're home.
Come in here.

01:36:30.218 --> 01:36:34.554
Listen to me.
I want you to tell this man...

01:36:34.556 --> 01:36:35.855
to make those people
go away.

01:36:35.857 --> 01:36:39.526
They're screaming
the most horrible things
that the children can hear them.

01:36:39.528 --> 01:36:41.895
Calm down, dear.
And he sits there.
He does nothing.

01:36:41.897 --> 01:36:45.064
He's not protecting us.
I want him out of the house.
Darling, calm down!

01:36:45.066 --> 01:36:48.568
Isn't this trespassing?
I don't want him here.
Come here.

01:36:48.570 --> 01:36:53.940
He's not protecting us.
Just calm down.
Calm down a second.

01:36:54.508 --> 01:36:56.943
Is your brother home?

01:36:56.945 --> 01:37:01.214
No.
He hasn't called, has he?

01:37:04.552 --> 01:37:06.319
All right.

01:37:06.321 --> 01:37:10.056
I think we should
leave New Rochelle
as soon as possible...

01:37:10.058 --> 01:37:12.025
and wait until
all of this calms down.

01:37:12.027 --> 01:37:15.428
Can you make the arrange--
What about my brother?
Where is he?

01:37:15.430 --> 01:37:17.063
Will he come too?
Your brother--

01:37:17.065 --> 01:37:20.900
your brother will do
what he wants to do,
as usual.

01:37:20.902 --> 01:37:25.605
Now, will you make arrangements
to close the house down?

01:37:47.161 --> 01:37:50.163
[ Doorbell Ringing ]

01:37:54.535 --> 01:37:57.103
[ Horse Nickers ]

01:38:05.346 --> 01:38:08.882
Wait a minute.
You can't leave that there.

01:38:24.231 --> 01:38:26.566
[ Dog Barking ]

01:38:45.352 --> 01:38:48.421
Don't turn around.
Just keep walking,
just like that.

01:38:48.423 --> 01:38:52.358
Don't turn around,
and you won't get hurt.

01:38:55.296 --> 01:38:57.563
Turn around.

01:38:57.932 --> 01:39:03.202
Now run and don't
look back. Run!
Don't look back!

01:39:04.638 --> 01:39:08.041
[ Approaching Hoofbeats ]

01:39:12.012 --> 01:39:14.681
[ Shouting ]
Whoa!

01:39:14.683 --> 01:39:17.083
Whoa! Whoa!

01:39:17.085 --> 01:39:19.652
Whoa!
Good boy, good boy.

01:39:33.334 --> 01:39:35.635
[ Chattering ]

01:39:40.174 --> 01:39:42.442
[ Quiet Chatter ]

01:39:42.444 --> 01:39:44.077
Come on.

01:39:44.079 --> 01:39:46.512
Come on!
Goddamn it!
Bust it.

01:39:46.514 --> 01:39:49.582
<i>Come on!</i>
<i>Bust it!</i>

01:39:50.551 --> 01:39:52.585
Bust it!

01:39:52.587 --> 01:39:55.455
[ Alarm Ringing ]

01:39:55.622 --> 01:39:59.092
<i>Well, come on!</i>
<i>Get it in!</i>
<i>Get it in!</i>

01:39:59.094 --> 01:40:02.628
All right.
Get rid of that wagon!

01:40:07.401 --> 01:40:09.402
Yah! Yah!

01:40:09.404 --> 01:40:11.637
Yah! Yah!

01:40:13.173 --> 01:40:16.042
[ Alarm Continues ]

01:40:16.044 --> 01:40:18.644
Come on!

01:40:36.663 --> 01:40:39.399
Stay back!

01:40:39.401 --> 01:40:42.135
Stay back, I said!

01:41:36.824 --> 01:41:39.692
[ Crying ]

01:41:46.433 --> 01:41:48.701
[ Man ]
Yes, give him that whack!
Try, Evelyn!

01:41:48.703 --> 01:41:52.371
Run! Run, run a bit!
Run a little bit!
Make run the feet!

01:41:52.373 --> 01:41:53.840
[ Shouting Gibberish ]

01:41:53.842 --> 01:41:58.878
<i>Evelyn, make a--</i>
<i>A little bit more angry!</i>
<i>More strained!</i>

01:41:58.880 --> 01:42:01.848
Open your eyes!
More! More angry!

01:42:01.850 --> 01:42:03.182
Okay, more, uh, uh--

01:42:03.184 --> 01:42:06.786
<i>You want to kill her!</i>
<i>You will kill her!</i>
<i>Evelyn!</i>

01:42:06.788 --> 01:42:09.388
Open your mouth!
You want to be more afraid!

01:42:09.390 --> 01:42:13.526
Open your mouth!
Open, open! Evelyn,
you want to be very afraid!

01:42:13.528 --> 01:42:16.496
<i>Extremely! Extremely!</i>

01:42:16.498 --> 01:42:20.199
[ Speaking Yiddish ]

01:42:35.716 --> 01:42:38.885
Play with your eye.
Play with your face.
Show with your tongue.

01:42:38.887 --> 01:42:42.421
Forget about the belly
or the "peedgy-peedgy"
with the feet.

01:42:42.423 --> 01:42:46.893
You understand?
Excellent. Wonderful.

01:42:47.794 --> 01:42:51.297
It's good?
Hello, young gentleman.

01:42:51.299 --> 01:42:53.799
Hello. Yes.
You saw the picture?
How do you like it?

01:42:53.801 --> 01:42:57.570
What are you doing?
Now, come along.
These people are working.

01:42:57.572 --> 01:42:59.605
He's your own son?
Yes.

01:42:59.607 --> 01:43:00.773
Very charming.
Oh, thank you.

01:43:00.775 --> 01:43:04.310
Very nice to see you.
I'm sorry. Now,
come along, please.

01:43:04.312 --> 01:43:07.613
Don't take him away.
Let him be here.

01:43:07.615 --> 01:43:11.617
That's my daughter.
How do you do?

01:43:11.619 --> 01:43:14.687
Say hello.

01:43:15.622 --> 01:43:17.657
He's shy.

01:43:17.659 --> 01:43:19.859
I'm shy too.

01:43:21.728 --> 01:43:24.597
You know what's it?
A book?

01:43:24.599 --> 01:43:28.601
It's... a majestic book.

01:43:31.371 --> 01:43:33.472
[ Imitates Explosion ]

01:43:33.474 --> 01:43:37.210
That's for you.
Take, take.
That's for you.

01:43:37.644 --> 01:43:40.646
Oh, no, no,
we couldn't do that.
Why?

01:43:40.648 --> 01:43:43.849
I give it like a present.

01:43:44.484 --> 01:43:46.219
Well, thank you.

01:43:46.221 --> 01:43:49.689
Is everything all right?
Yes.

01:43:49.691 --> 01:43:51.824
This is my husband.

01:43:51.826 --> 01:43:56.495
Very nice.
My, uh, name,
Baron Ashkenazy.

01:43:56.497 --> 01:43:59.265
My "gratulation" to you.
Baron. Uh, pardon?

01:43:59.267 --> 01:44:04.971
My "gratulation."
You have very nice wife,
and your son is wonderful.

01:44:05.939 --> 01:44:08.741
Oh, oh, I see.
Thank you.

01:44:09.676 --> 01:44:11.644
- Can you dance, my little?
- Yes.

01:44:11.646 --> 01:44:13.946
We'll finish on the film
and I'll make a party.

01:44:13.948 --> 01:44:19.252
And you'll be my guest,
and you'll be together
with my daughter.

01:44:19.886 --> 01:44:22.922
And you'll be
all my guest.
Oh.

01:44:22.924 --> 01:44:26.959
Well, if, uh, we're
still here, perhaps.
Oh.

01:44:26.961 --> 01:44:30.496
I forget to introduce you
with my better,

01:44:30.498 --> 01:44:33.366
with my star,
Evelyn Nesbit.

01:44:33.368 --> 01:44:35.768
She's, uh, very, uh--

01:44:35.770 --> 01:44:37.503
a great talent.

01:44:37.505 --> 01:44:38.604
I hope she'll
make me great.

01:44:38.606 --> 01:44:44.910
It's very nice to meet you.
We read about you in the papers.
You're very beautiful.

01:44:44.912 --> 01:44:46.812
Thank you.

01:44:46.980 --> 01:44:51.384
It's high time to continue
our work. If you want to,
you can watch our film.

01:44:51.386 --> 01:44:54.787
We don't forbid you.
Evelyn, come.

01:44:55.989 --> 01:45:00.459
Evelyn!
Would you please, Evelyn?
We have the light!

01:45:04.765 --> 01:45:09.568
[ Dog Barking ]
[ Indistinct Shouting ]

01:45:25.752 --> 01:45:28.387
You all set, Captain?
The whole building
is covered.

01:45:28.389 --> 01:45:33.392
And I've got three groups of
five men ready to hit the place
simultaneously.

01:45:33.394 --> 01:45:34.994
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Let me through.</i>

01:45:34.996 --> 01:45:38.397
Let me through!
That's impossible, gentlemen.

01:45:38.399 --> 01:45:41.100
<i>That's simply</i>
<i>out of the question.</i>
<i>Who's he?</i>

01:45:41.102 --> 01:45:43.569
- I'm Mr. Vernon Elliott.
- Vernon Elliott.

01:45:43.571 --> 01:45:47.707
He's the curator
for the Morgan Library.

01:45:47.709 --> 01:45:49.709
What can I do for you,
Mr. Elliott?

01:45:49.711 --> 01:45:51.644
That place
is a national treasure,

01:45:51.646 --> 01:45:55.648
and if this climate
of violence continues,
I shall go to the president.

01:45:55.650 --> 01:45:59.585
- You will, huh?
- Indeed I will,
if I deem it necessary.

01:45:59.587 --> 01:46:03.723
By the way,
I'm Rheinlander Waldo,
commissioner of police.

01:46:03.725 --> 01:46:05.558
Yes? Well, I'm honored.

01:46:05.560 --> 01:46:08.861
And if any harm comes
to any object in that building,

01:46:08.863 --> 01:46:12.565
with all due respect,
there'll be grave consequences.

01:46:12.567 --> 01:46:16.802
How many are in there?
[ Officer ] We're not sure yet.
At least two.

01:46:16.804 --> 01:46:18.738
Maybe more--
maybe much more.

01:46:18.740 --> 01:46:21.640
But who are they?
What are they up to?

01:46:21.642 --> 01:46:23.843
Zero.

01:46:24.010 --> 01:46:30.416
Well, Mr. Elliott,
why don't you go in and have
a word with them?

01:46:30.584 --> 01:46:33.819
- I beg your pardon.
- Just explain the value
of the library,

01:46:33.821 --> 01:46:36.088
see what they want--
that sort of thing.

01:46:36.090 --> 01:46:39.959
That hardly seems
like the appropriate procedure,
Mr. Waldo.

01:46:39.961 --> 01:46:41.794
And if you're making a joke
at my expense,

01:46:41.796 --> 01:46:46.499
I assure you
there's nothing amusing
about my responsibilities...

01:46:46.501 --> 01:46:48.701
<i>as the curator</i>
<i>of Mr. Morgan's library.</i>

01:46:48.703 --> 01:46:53.172
Mr. Elliott... as long
as those guys are in there,

01:46:53.174 --> 01:46:58.077
you are not the curator
of anything.

01:46:58.079 --> 01:47:00.679
Give me a megaphone.

01:47:01.148 --> 01:47:04.016
[ Whistle Blowing ]

01:47:04.018 --> 01:47:06.919
[ Dogs Barking ]

01:47:17.063 --> 01:47:21.867
I am Rheinlander Waldo.
I am Commissioner of Police.

01:47:21.869 --> 01:47:24.570
I'm going to walk toward you.

01:47:24.572 --> 01:47:25.938
I am not armed.

01:47:25.940 --> 01:47:29.608
I want to talk to you.
Can you hear me?

01:47:29.610 --> 01:47:32.511
I want to talk to you
inside the library.

01:47:32.513 --> 01:47:36.749
If you'll let me come in,
please open the door
as I approach.

01:47:36.751 --> 01:47:41.153
I am not armed as you can see.
<i>[ Door Opens ]</i>

01:47:42.856 --> 01:47:46.692
- <i>[ Dog Barking ]</i>
<i>-[ Man Shouting ]</i>
<i> Cover!</i>

01:47:46.694 --> 01:47:49.028
[ Whistle Blowing ]
Come on!

01:47:49.030 --> 01:47:54.700
That's it! Fall back!
That's it! Come on.
Down there. That's it. Back!

01:48:00.474 --> 01:48:02.508
What was that?

01:48:02.510 --> 01:48:07.079
Let me have that, please.
Please, please.

01:48:07.081 --> 01:48:08.914
My God!

01:48:08.916 --> 01:48:11.817
Tsk! That's a covered goblet.

01:48:11.819 --> 01:48:16.689
- What?
- It's from the 17th century.

01:48:16.691 --> 01:48:19.892
Commissioned
by Frederick of Saxony.

01:48:19.894 --> 01:48:23.262
<i>It's silver</i>
<i>inlaid with gold...</i>

01:48:23.264 --> 01:48:26.665
and studded
with precious gems.

01:48:28.768 --> 01:48:31.770
Captain, go get it.

01:48:32.873 --> 01:48:34.974
Sergeant.

01:48:34.976 --> 01:48:37.142
Sir.

01:48:51.525 --> 01:48:52.858
Sir.

01:48:52.860 --> 01:48:56.295
Captain, open it.
Sergeant.

01:49:08.575 --> 01:49:12.111
Well, what is it?
"Murray Hill, 8529."

01:49:12.113 --> 01:49:16.081
- What? That's my number.
- What?

01:49:16.083 --> 01:49:19.985
- My office in the library.
- Good.

01:49:19.987 --> 01:49:21.954
<i>[ Doorbell Ringing ]</i>
<i>[ Banging On Door ]</i>

01:49:21.956 --> 01:49:25.624
I'll get it, ma'am.
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Police. Open up.</i>

01:49:25.626 --> 01:49:26.759
<i>[ Door Opens ]</i>

01:49:26.761 --> 01:49:30.930
Do you have a telephone?
We had nothing to do with it.

01:49:30.932 --> 01:49:33.232
Do you have a telephone?
Yes, of course we do.

01:49:33.234 --> 01:49:34.867
Where? Thank you.
In there.

01:49:34.869 --> 01:49:37.670
There's the one upstairs,
but it's out of order.

01:49:37.672 --> 01:49:40.272
[ Man ]
Ma'am, I would like you to sign
this formal release.

01:49:40.274 --> 01:49:42.875
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>What are all these</i>
<i>policemen doing here?</i>

01:49:42.877 --> 01:49:45.210
<i>I've never seen so many</i>
<i>policemen in my life!</i>

01:49:45.212 --> 01:49:47.346
I cannot understand this!
We'll deal with it later.

01:49:47.348 --> 01:49:50.616
Where are they going?
You can't go in there.

01:49:50.618 --> 01:49:51.984
I want to go in my house.

01:49:51.986 --> 01:49:55.220
It's my own room in there.
What do you mean,
I can't go in there?

01:49:55.222 --> 01:49:59.758
What are they doing in there
that they don't want me to see
them doing?

01:49:59.760 --> 01:50:03.729
<i>[ Captain ]</i>
<i>Central, this is</i>
<i>a police emergency.</i>

01:50:03.731 --> 01:50:05.898
<i>Give me Murray Hill, 8529.</i>

01:50:05.900 --> 01:50:09.902
[ Operator ]
Repeat that, please.
I repeat, Murray Hill, 8529.

01:50:09.904 --> 01:50:12.171
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>I don't understand this,</i>
<i>and I'm a moral woman.</i>

01:50:12.173 --> 01:50:16.108
I don't want anything going on
in this house I don't know
anything about.

01:50:16.110 --> 01:50:17.343
Please open up the door.
Yes.

01:50:17.345 --> 01:50:22.114
Sir?
<i>Oh, I never saw anything</i>
<i>like this in my life.</i>

01:50:22.116 --> 01:50:24.717
Hello. This is
Rheinlander Waldo speaking.

01:50:24.719 --> 01:50:29.955
[ Walker ] Mr. Waldo,
I want my car returned in
the same condition it was in...

01:50:29.957 --> 01:50:31.724
when my way was blocked.

01:50:31.726 --> 01:50:33.859
In return for the life
of my Sarah,

01:50:33.861 --> 01:50:38.697
I want Fire Chief Willie Conklin
turned over to my justice.

01:50:38.699 --> 01:50:40.132
Is that clear?

01:50:40.134 --> 01:50:43.402
Who is this?
Who am I speaking to?

01:50:43.837 --> 01:50:46.372
You're speaking
to Coalhouse Walker, Jr.

01:50:46.374 --> 01:50:48.674
You have 48 hours
to meet my demands.

01:50:48.676 --> 01:50:55.114
I should warn you
that this entire building
has been mined with explosives.

01:50:56.349 --> 01:50:58.651
[ Line Disconnects ]

01:50:58.653 --> 01:51:02.354
Hello! Hello?

01:51:02.356 --> 01:51:04.657
Get that number again,
will you?

01:51:04.659 --> 01:51:07.026
That's the crazy buck
from New Rochelle, isn't it?

01:51:07.028 --> 01:51:12.197
- I think so.
- Oh, boy, oh, boy,
oh, boy, oh, boy.

01:51:12.199 --> 01:51:13.232
Captain.

01:51:13.234 --> 01:51:16.702
- Get the police chief
from New Rochelle down here.
- Right.

01:51:16.704 --> 01:51:19.772
And I want blueprints
of the library and
an explosives man.

01:51:19.774 --> 01:51:21.740
- Yes, sir.
- Get the militia ready.

01:51:21.742 --> 01:51:24.109
- Right.
- Where is J.P. Morgan?

01:51:24.111 --> 01:51:29.448
Oh, he's on an expedition
down the Nile... in Egypt.

01:51:29.450 --> 01:51:33.318
- Hmm. Lucky him.
- Yes, sir.

01:51:33.320 --> 01:51:39.291
And contact some colored
big shots to talk for us
in case we need to negotiate.

01:51:39.293 --> 01:51:41.393
Very good, sir.
Anything else?

01:51:41.395 --> 01:51:45.097
Yeah. He said something
about a car and a fire chief.

01:51:45.099 --> 01:51:47.099
Conklin. Willie Conklin.

01:51:47.101 --> 01:51:48.434
Get him in.
I want to meet him.

01:51:48.436 --> 01:51:52.805
Sir, that number doesn't answer.
What do you want me to do?

01:51:54.040 --> 01:51:56.942
Get me some coffee and a roll.
Yes, sir.

01:51:56.944 --> 01:52:01.013
[ Crowd ]
♪ Does Jesus bear

01:52:01.015 --> 01:52:04.383
♪ The cross alone

01:52:04.385 --> 01:52:08.320
♪ And all the world

01:52:08.322 --> 01:52:11.390
♪ Go free

01:52:11.392 --> 01:52:14.226
♪ Now there's a cross ♪

01:52:14.228 --> 01:52:18.430
♪ For everyone
What do you people think
about this?  Mr. Washington!

01:52:18.432 --> 01:52:22.434
♪ And there's a cross ♪
Mr. Washington!

01:52:22.436 --> 01:52:24.737
♪ For me

01:52:24.739 --> 01:52:28.207
I want you to know
how much we appreciate this,
Mr. Washington.

01:52:28.209 --> 01:52:30.776
I hope and pray
that his mind is open to reason.

01:52:30.778 --> 01:52:33.746
Now, you don't have to
do this if you don't want to.

01:52:33.748 --> 01:52:36.215
I'm ready, Mr. Waldo.

01:52:37.283 --> 01:52:41.787
You're a brave man, sir.
You have my blessing.

01:52:44.023 --> 01:52:45.891
[ Woman ]
♪ What

01:52:45.893 --> 01:52:50.896
♪ A friend we have in Jesus

01:52:50.898 --> 01:52:56.869
♪ All our sins and griefs
to bear ♪

01:52:56.871 --> 01:53:03.509
♪ What a privilege to carry

01:53:03.511 --> 01:53:09.414
♪ Everything to God in prayer

01:53:09.416 --> 01:53:13.152
I think you know me by name,
Mr. Walker.

01:53:13.154 --> 01:53:14.820
Open the door!

01:53:14.822 --> 01:53:19.124
In the name of our people,
open the door!

01:53:56.396 --> 01:54:01.133
[ Walker ]
I'm honored to meet you,
Mr. Washington.

01:54:02.235 --> 01:54:05.204
Would you care for a seat?

01:54:28.328 --> 01:54:31.096
You seem to know about me.

01:54:31.865 --> 01:54:34.299
Of course I do.

01:54:34.301 --> 01:54:37.636
I have a great admiration
for you, sir.

01:54:37.638 --> 01:54:40.372
- Truly?
- Yes, sir.

01:54:40.540 --> 01:54:43.342
How can you say that
when your actions...

01:54:43.344 --> 01:54:47.212
are a mockery
of everything I stand for?

01:54:50.316 --> 01:54:53.051
I had no choice in that, sir.

01:54:53.053 --> 01:54:54.052
Mr. Walker,

01:54:54.054 --> 01:55:00.926
I have spent a lifetime
trying to persuade the white man
that he needn't fear us--

01:55:01.094 --> 01:55:03.629
that all we wanted
was a chance to work...

01:55:03.631 --> 01:55:05.497
and prosper beside him...

01:55:05.499 --> 01:55:09.368
and enjoy with him
the fruits of this great land.

01:55:09.370 --> 01:55:13.071
Now, the example of 1,000...

01:55:13.073 --> 01:55:16.174
honest, industrious black men...

01:55:16.176 --> 01:55:19.344
cannot undo the harm
of one like you.

01:55:19.346 --> 01:55:23.282
What you have done here
has set our race back...

01:55:23.284 --> 01:55:27.185
a distance I can't measure.

01:55:27.620 --> 01:55:31.957
And you say... you admire me.

01:55:32.258 --> 01:55:34.226
I tried everything, sir--

01:55:34.228 --> 01:55:38.697
every legal means
to get satisfaction--

01:55:38.699 --> 01:55:42.367
and I was humiliated
at every turn.

01:55:43.036 --> 01:55:46.004
<i>The woman who bore</i>
<i>my child--</i>

01:55:46.006 --> 01:55:49.041
my child, Mr. Washington,

01:55:49.275 --> 01:55:52.444
whom I may never see again--

01:55:55.081 --> 01:55:59.551
she watched my pride
being snatched away from me,

01:55:59.553 --> 01:56:02.054
piece by piece.

01:56:05.391 --> 01:56:09.594
She believed in justice.

01:56:09.596 --> 01:56:11.997
Oh, yes.

01:56:13.199 --> 01:56:15.968
She went to the white man,
and she begged...

01:56:15.970 --> 01:56:20.072
that I be given the justice
entitled to me by law.

01:56:26.212 --> 01:56:29.281
She died begging for it.

01:56:32.452 --> 01:56:37.089
I... beg you, Mr. Walker,

01:56:37.390 --> 01:56:40.425
on behalf of our people,

01:56:40.427 --> 01:56:42.094
your young son...

01:56:42.096 --> 01:56:44.763
and all the children
of our race--

01:56:44.765 --> 01:56:48.433
I beg you to give yourself up.

01:56:48.634 --> 01:56:52.037
Bring your men
and follow me now.

01:56:52.039 --> 01:56:54.639
I will intercede on your behalf.

01:56:54.641 --> 01:56:57.609
Your trial... shall be swift...

01:56:57.611 --> 01:57:01.380
and your execution painless.

01:57:07.153 --> 01:57:10.655
If my automobile is restored...

01:57:10.657 --> 01:57:15.127
and delivered
to the front of this building...

01:57:15.762 --> 01:57:20.232
and the fire chief
is handed over to <i>my</i> justice,

01:57:20.234 --> 01:57:22.734
[ Sighs ]
I give you my solemn oath...

01:57:22.736 --> 01:57:24.669
<i>I will come out</i>
<i>with my hands raised...</i>

01:57:24.671 --> 01:57:29.307
<i>and no further harm</i>
<i>will come to this place</i>
<i>or to any man.</i>

01:57:29.309 --> 01:57:33.545
And you think this revenge
will restore your damaged pride?

01:57:33.547 --> 01:57:35.247
I wouldn't be here
if I didn't think so.

01:57:35.249 --> 01:57:39.317
Well, you are wrong, Mr. Walker.
You are wrong to the depths
of your soul.

01:57:39.319 --> 01:57:42.788
- Why do you say that?
- Because vengeance
does nothing...

01:57:42.790 --> 01:57:45.323
but perpetuate more vengeance
and on and on...

01:57:45.325 --> 01:57:49.461
until some race can find
the strength to say, "No!

01:57:49.463 --> 01:57:52.597
"The wrong done to me
I will not avenge!

01:57:52.599 --> 01:57:57.235
"I shall stand with dignity
and Christian love...

01:57:57.237 --> 01:57:59.438
"until my enemies
are won over...

01:57:59.440 --> 01:58:03.241
because they honor
and respect me."

01:58:03.243 --> 01:58:06.545
And only when this happens,
Mr. Walker,

01:58:06.547 --> 01:58:09.481
shall we have our pride back.

01:58:10.483 --> 01:58:12.717
All of us.

01:58:15.788 --> 01:58:18.256
[ Laughing ]

01:58:18.691 --> 01:58:25.263
My God, if only Sarah
could be here to listen to you.

01:58:26.599 --> 01:58:31.336
She thought
I had a mouth on <i>me.</i>
<i>[ Sighs ]</i>

01:58:31.338 --> 01:58:35.440
But you speak like an angel,
Mr. Washington.

01:58:38.244 --> 01:58:44.216
[ Sighs ]
It's too bad we're living...
on the earth.

01:58:48.121 --> 01:58:50.689
You are damned,

01:58:50.691 --> 01:58:53.191
Mr. Walker.

01:58:54.861 --> 01:58:57.596
[ Indistinct Chattering ]

01:59:01.300 --> 01:59:03.135
Sir.

01:59:03.137 --> 01:59:05.570
We're starting, sir.

01:59:54.954 --> 01:59:59.424
- <i>[ Man Screams ]</i>
<i>-[ Glass Shatters ]</i>

02:00:06.566 --> 02:00:08.800
[ Waldo ]
Goddamn it!

02:00:08.802 --> 02:00:12.204
♪ [ Ragtime ]

02:00:14.340 --> 02:00:16.841
<i>[ Glass Clinking ]</i>
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Your ear!</i>

02:00:16.843 --> 02:00:20.545
Your ear!
Your ear, your ear!

02:00:20.547 --> 02:00:23.515
My dear guests,
today we celebrate...

02:00:23.517 --> 02:00:26.685
<i>the ending</i>
<i>of my third photoplay.</i>

02:00:26.687 --> 02:00:30.822
My first photoplay had called
The Naive Daughter.

02:00:30.824 --> 02:00:35.760
<i>It cost me $500</i>
<i>and the profit was $10,000.</i>

02:00:35.762 --> 02:00:40.365
<i>The second was even better</i>
<i>than the first,</i>

02:00:40.367 --> 02:00:42.000
<i>and the profit was more.</i>

02:00:42.002 --> 02:00:45.670
<i>Now,</i>
<i>my toast is for this...</i>

02:00:45.672 --> 02:00:49.341
what make me possible
to do everything.

02:00:50.443 --> 02:00:52.744
Do you know what's it? Light.

02:00:52.746 --> 02:00:57.382
You see the light of the candle?
It's very nice.

02:00:57.384 --> 02:01:01.486
It shine through the glass.

02:01:01.488 --> 02:01:06.424
It's refract.
The chandelier. It's convert.

02:01:06.426 --> 02:01:10.262
It's transferring.
Small star.

02:01:10.563 --> 02:01:14.399
And now we make pictures
from the light.

02:01:14.401 --> 02:01:17.469
People pay a couple of penny
and they watch,

02:01:17.471 --> 02:01:20.705
in a short time,
the whole life of man--

02:01:20.707 --> 02:01:27.379
how they fight, how they eat,
how they lo-love.

02:01:28.547 --> 02:01:34.052
It's no limits for our
opportunities in the photoplay.

02:01:37.523 --> 02:01:40.859
And now we have a dance, please.

02:02:27.673 --> 02:02:32.344
Dear, you remember
these gentlemen?
They're police.

02:02:32.346 --> 02:02:33.978
Yes.

02:02:33.980 --> 02:02:37.048
Well, uh,
the feeling seems to be--

02:02:37.050 --> 02:02:43.121
Well, they'd like to take
Mr. Walker's baby back
to New York with them.

02:02:47.026 --> 02:02:51.996
Why?
We don't get explanations,
ma'am. We get orders.

02:02:51.998 --> 02:02:54.432
Well, that doesn't
entitle you...

02:02:54.434 --> 02:02:57.969
to just come along
and take a child away
without giving any reasons.

02:02:57.971 --> 02:03:03.108
We're dealing with an extremely
dangerous criminal, ma'am.
You realize that, don't you?

02:03:03.110 --> 02:03:08.012
What does that have
to do with it? We're talking
about the baby, not the father.

02:03:08.014 --> 02:03:11.483
Ma'am, we don't have time to
stand around and talk it over.

02:03:11.485 --> 02:03:12.984
If you want reasons, take it up
with the commissioner.

02:03:12.986 --> 02:03:18.623
If he would like to explain
to me why he wants the child,
I'd be happy to listen.

02:03:18.625 --> 02:03:21.559
We have a job to do.
Are you going to let us do it?

02:03:21.561 --> 02:03:24.462
I'm not trying to stop you
from doing your job.

02:03:24.464 --> 02:03:26.831
I'm afraid that's exactly
what you are doing.

02:03:26.833 --> 02:03:30.001
Now, just a minute, gentlemen.
There's no need for that.

02:03:30.003 --> 02:03:33.938
What my wife means is
that she is conc--
What I mean...

02:03:33.940 --> 02:03:37.142
is they cannot have
that baby...

02:03:37.144 --> 02:03:39.477
until we get an explanation.

02:03:39.479 --> 02:03:41.646
You're making it
very difficult, ma'am.

02:03:41.648 --> 02:03:45.617
Well...
I'm sorry about that.

02:03:45.619 --> 02:03:50.188
Gentlemen, would you please
wait for us in the lobby?

02:03:50.190 --> 02:03:54.526
<i>I want a word with my wife.</i>

02:04:01.600 --> 02:04:04.002
Dear, this is becoming absurd.

02:04:04.004 --> 02:04:07.105
They have no right
to bother us.

02:04:07.107 --> 02:04:11.476
That's not the point.
We're involved now.

02:04:11.478 --> 02:04:14.746
In their eyes,
we're helping Walker.

02:04:14.748 --> 02:04:17.148
Well, then they're just
being ridiculous.

02:04:17.150 --> 02:04:22.020
No, <i>we're</i> being ridiculous
if we don't protect ourselves.

02:04:22.022 --> 02:04:25.190
But we are innocent.

02:04:26.892 --> 02:04:29.928
[ Sighs ]
All right.

02:04:30.062 --> 02:04:34.165
If that's the way
you're going to be,
I'm going back to New York,

02:04:34.167 --> 02:04:36.935
with or without the baby.

02:04:37.636 --> 02:04:41.739
Oh, please...

02:04:41.741 --> 02:04:44.008
don't go.

02:04:45.077 --> 02:04:49.113
Please don't
leave me here alone.

02:05:06.165 --> 02:05:11.135
All right, Conklin.
Hold it right where you are.
You're under arrest! Take him.

02:05:11.137 --> 02:05:13.071
No, no, no, no!
You're making a mistake!

02:05:13.073 --> 02:05:16.975
For God's sake,
I'm not Conklin.
You're making a mistake!

02:05:16.977 --> 02:05:19.777
- There's the man you want!
- You son of a bitch!

02:05:19.779 --> 02:05:25.149
- Hold it!
Take that one out too!
- <i>[ Old Man ] My God!</i>

02:05:34.226 --> 02:05:36.861
All right. Come on.

02:05:37.563 --> 02:05:40.865
All right. Come on.
Straighten up, Willie.

02:05:40.867 --> 02:05:42.967
Are you ready, Mr. Conklin?

02:05:42.969 --> 02:05:45.203
Ready? Ready for what?
What do you mean?

02:05:45.205 --> 02:05:49.307
You know that someone's been
asking for you, don't you?

02:05:50.676 --> 02:05:52.010
What is this?

02:05:52.012 --> 02:05:55.046
It's a joke, huh?
It's a joke, right?

02:05:55.048 --> 02:05:57.048
No joke, Willie.

02:05:57.050 --> 02:06:00.818
The library over there
is worth millions.

02:06:00.986 --> 02:06:04.689
- So?
- And people keep telling me...

02:06:04.691 --> 02:06:06.624
you're a worthless piece
of slime.

02:06:06.626 --> 02:06:08.993
Hold him back!
Can't talk to me like that!

02:06:08.995 --> 02:06:13.131
Shut up, Willie.
You're going to help us now.

02:06:13.133 --> 02:06:14.999
You're going to talk
to that troublemaker,

02:06:15.001 --> 02:06:16.968
and I mean talk hard
like you never talked before.

02:06:16.970 --> 02:06:23.141
Because he wants you, Willie.
And if you can't make him change
his demands,

02:06:23.143 --> 02:06:24.909
he's gonna get you.

02:06:24.911 --> 02:06:28.980
I don't have to do this.
I want a lawyer.

02:06:30.182 --> 02:06:34.319
- Waldo. Library, please.
- I got my rights, you know!

02:06:34.321 --> 02:06:36.821
Walker?
Speaking.

02:06:36.823 --> 02:06:39.791
We have the fire chief
for you.

02:06:40.326 --> 02:06:43.094
<i>Send him over.</i>

02:06:43.096 --> 02:06:45.163
Take it.

02:06:45.165 --> 02:06:48.333
[ Gasping ]
Release him.

02:06:50.135 --> 02:06:52.003
Hey, listen to me,
you crazy nigger.

02:06:52.005 --> 02:06:53.705
<i>I've had enough of you,</i>
<i>you hear me?</i>

02:06:53.707 --> 02:06:57.742
<i>You can't be thinking</i>
<i>that they're gonna give me</i>
<i>to the likes of you.</i>

02:06:57.744 --> 02:07:01.179
No. I know you--
I-I know you ain't that stupid.

02:07:01.181 --> 02:07:03.214
No. You're one of them
smart niggers.

02:07:03.216 --> 02:07:05.350
<i>So how'd you ever own</i>
<i>a car like that, huh?</i>

02:07:05.352 --> 02:07:07.018
<i>So what do you say we just</i>
<i>talk this thing over?</i>

02:07:07.020 --> 02:07:11.789
Yeah, I'm ready to do that.
I'll go halfway with you
on this thing. I don't mind.

02:07:11.791 --> 02:07:14.192
Sort of like you come on over,
we'll sit down.

02:07:14.194 --> 02:07:15.793
<i>Have a nice talk, huh?</i>
<i>What do you say?</i>

02:07:15.795 --> 02:07:20.098
Look, the commissioner here
says he'll leave us alone.
Gave me his word.

02:07:20.100 --> 02:07:23.735
<i>What do you say, Walker?</i>

02:07:24.903 --> 02:07:26.771
Goddamn it, say something!

02:07:26.773 --> 02:07:30.041
It was a joke, damn you!
Can't you even take a joke?

02:07:30.043 --> 02:07:33.645
You can't talk
to that nigger bastard!

02:07:36.882 --> 02:07:40.785
Jesus to hell!
Say something, would you?

02:07:42.254 --> 02:07:46.724
Let me speak to Waldo.
He wants to talk to you.

02:07:52.231 --> 02:07:54.432
Waldo.

02:07:54.800 --> 02:07:58.670
- <i>Send him over.</i>
<i>- Walker, listen to me--</i>

02:07:58.672 --> 02:08:01.072
[ Line Disconnects ]

02:08:11.016 --> 02:08:14.686
What? No. What do you think
you're doing? No!

02:08:14.688 --> 02:08:16.788
You're not taking me over there!

02:08:16.790 --> 02:08:22.460
Let go of me, you goons!
Let go of me! You want to find
your houses burning?

02:08:22.462 --> 02:08:24.829
[ Indistinct ]

02:08:24.831 --> 02:08:25.997
You'll see! You'll see!

02:08:25.999 --> 02:08:28.866
Touch one of us, you mess with
every fireman in the country!

02:08:28.868 --> 02:08:32.070
Can't somebody please tell me
what is going on?

02:08:32.072 --> 02:08:33.738
Can you just give me
a rough idea?

02:08:33.740 --> 02:08:36.841
[ Whispering ]
There's not gonna be
a fireman left in sight.

02:08:36.843 --> 02:08:39.143
Good. Tell him
I want to see him right away.

02:08:39.145 --> 02:08:43.047
Would everyone please leave
the room? Thank you.

02:08:43.049 --> 02:08:44.916
Gentlemen? Hurry, please.

02:08:44.918 --> 02:08:47.919
Mr. Elliott, please.
Thank you.

02:08:49.288 --> 02:08:52.256
Thank you. Yes.

02:08:52.258 --> 02:08:55.259
The commissioner
will see you now.

02:08:56.895 --> 02:08:59.063
Jim.

02:09:19.251 --> 02:09:22.286
[ Phone Ringing ]

02:09:24.389 --> 02:09:27.024
[ Ringing Continues ]

02:09:39.238 --> 02:09:43.875
Yes? Yes, I'll speak to him.

02:09:53.452 --> 02:09:55.253
Um, Mr. Walker?

02:09:55.255 --> 02:09:58.189
Hello, sir.
How are you?

02:09:59.224 --> 02:10:02.560
Fine. Um--

02:10:03.328 --> 02:10:06.531
I'd like very much
to have a word with you.

02:10:06.533 --> 02:10:10.168
Would it be all right
if I came over?

02:10:16.074 --> 02:10:18.810
Yes. That'll be fine.

02:10:23.515 --> 02:10:26.250
It's your brother-in-law.

02:10:29.021 --> 02:10:31.189
He wants me to come over.

02:10:31.191 --> 02:10:34.425
Now you know
I can't take the responsibility.

02:10:34.427 --> 02:10:36.994
Yes. Yes, I know.

02:10:40.999 --> 02:10:46.404
- I want to go.
- Okay.

02:11:55.908 --> 02:11:59.076
You're a brave man.

02:11:59.244 --> 02:12:02.647
May I ask you a question,
Mr. Walker?

02:12:02.649 --> 02:12:04.682
I can't stop you from asking.

02:12:04.684 --> 02:12:08.319
Do you remember
my brother-in-law--

02:12:08.321 --> 02:12:11.555
the young man
you met at my house?

02:12:11.557 --> 02:12:13.925
Yes. Yes, I believe I do.

02:12:13.927 --> 02:12:18.562
-Was he ever in touch with you?
-Is that why you came over here?

02:12:19.364 --> 02:12:22.433
Well, in-- in part, yes.

02:12:23.602 --> 02:12:26.270
What's the other part?
Well,

02:12:26.272 --> 02:12:30.274
I... hoped, since we've...

02:12:30.276 --> 02:12:33.577
known each other
under better circumstances--

02:12:33.579 --> 02:12:39.984
I hoped I might prevail on you
to change your--

02:12:42.587 --> 02:12:45.256
on you to ch--

02:12:47.192 --> 02:12:49.694
<i>to change your mind.</i>

02:12:54.099 --> 02:12:56.334
I haven't seen
your brother-in-law.

02:12:56.336 --> 02:13:01.205
<i>But you can go back</i>
<i>and tell Mr. Waldo that</i>
<i>I have changed my mind.</i>

02:13:01.207 --> 02:13:03.441
I'm ready to offer him a swap--

02:13:03.443 --> 02:13:05.443
Conklin's life
for the freedom of my men.

02:13:05.445 --> 02:13:09.347
<i>All he's got to do</i>
<i>is deliver my automobile...</i>

02:13:09.349 --> 02:13:11.082
to the front door
of this library.

02:13:11.084 --> 02:13:16.120
And when it's dark, my men
will use it to get out of here.

02:13:16.722 --> 02:13:18.589
When they're safe...

02:13:18.591 --> 02:13:21.092
and sure they haven't
been followed,

02:13:21.094 --> 02:13:23.561
they'll call me here.

02:13:24.363 --> 02:13:28.599
<i>And I'll come out</i>
<i>with my hands up.</i>
<i>[ Man ] Hey, Coalhouse!</i>

02:13:28.601 --> 02:13:32.036
You be quiet, you hear?

02:13:34.773 --> 02:13:37.708
Tell Mr. Waldo that if he
plays it straight with me...

02:13:37.710 --> 02:13:41.245
that's exactly
how it will happen.

02:13:41.546 --> 02:13:45.116
- You remember that?
- Yes.

02:13:45.417 --> 02:13:49.153
- I th-- Yeah, I think so.
- Good.

02:14:04.603 --> 02:14:07.671
<i>Hey, brother. What is this?</i>
<i>You playing games with us?</i>

02:14:07.673 --> 02:14:13.210
Why you sayin' like
we leavin' without you? You know
that ain't gonna happen.

02:14:13.212 --> 02:14:15.813
[ Chuckles ]
Zeke, you're a hothead.

02:14:15.815 --> 02:14:20.117
You gotta calm down or else
your brains are gonna burn up.

02:14:20.119 --> 02:14:21.585
Well, you said it.

02:14:21.587 --> 02:14:23.287
I mean, Coalhouse,
didn't you say--

02:14:23.289 --> 02:14:27.758
didn't you say that you were
gonna stay right here, huh?

02:14:27.760 --> 02:14:30.494
I said a lot of things.

02:14:34.366 --> 02:14:38.769
[ Chuckles ]
Then you're messin' with 'em.

02:14:38.771 --> 02:14:42.473
You-- you got
somethin' else in mind.

02:14:42.475 --> 02:14:44.175
You see that, Zeke?

02:14:44.177 --> 02:14:49.380
When you calm down,
your brain starts to worki''
just fine.

02:14:49.382 --> 02:14:52.750
Yeah. Yeah!

02:14:52.752 --> 02:14:56.787
I don't get it.
I just don't get it.

02:14:56.789 --> 02:14:59.123
It doesn't make sense to me.

02:14:59.125 --> 02:15:01.158
He seemed perfectly rational
and coherent to me.

02:15:01.160 --> 02:15:06.363
Well, maybe he thinks
he can sneak into the car and
escape with the rest of them.

02:15:06.365 --> 02:15:09.700
Well, it'll be night,
it'll be dark.

02:15:09.702 --> 02:15:13.204
He can't leave
the library alone.

02:15:13.206 --> 02:15:14.738
That's all he's got.

02:15:14.740 --> 02:15:19.510
The second we know it's empty,
we can blast that car to bits.

02:15:20.378 --> 02:15:24.682
No. We can't do it.
We can't buy his terms.

02:15:24.684 --> 02:15:26.684
Why not?
Look.

02:15:26.686 --> 02:15:27.685
Let's say his men got away.

02:15:27.687 --> 02:15:33.791
All right. There he is,
sitting on the detonator
and he knows he's a dead man.

02:15:34.159 --> 02:15:37.761
The only freedom he's got left
is how to die.

02:15:37.763 --> 02:15:39.463
He can let us fry him
in the electric chair,

02:15:39.465 --> 02:15:43.734
or he can go "bang" and carry
the library to heaven with him.

02:15:43.736 --> 02:15:46.704
I disagree.

02:15:46.706 --> 02:15:48.172
Why?

02:15:48.174 --> 02:15:50.374
I believe he means
what he says.

02:15:50.376 --> 02:15:51.408
Well, that's damn big of you,

02:15:51.410 --> 02:15:55.513
but I'm afraid your belief
isn't the iron-plated guarantee
that I need here!

02:15:55.515 --> 02:15:58.482
Well, what if I was
in the library...

02:15:58.484 --> 02:16:01.185
<i>until Mr. Walker</i>
<i>gave himself up?</i>

02:16:01.187 --> 02:16:03.287
Would that be
sufficient guarantee?

02:16:03.289 --> 02:16:07.558
Be a guarantee
that you're as crazy as he is.

02:16:07.560 --> 02:16:09.527
Are you on the level?

02:16:09.529 --> 02:16:10.461
Yes!
You're saying...

02:16:10.463 --> 02:16:13.664
you'd volunteer to go over there
and get yourself blown up
with that crazy buck?

02:16:13.666 --> 02:16:18.402
I believe if you keep your word
and let his men go free,
I'll have nothing to fear.

02:16:18.404 --> 02:16:21.872
Why, for Christ's sake?
What are you to him?

02:16:21.874 --> 02:16:24.642
I'm no judge of these things,
Mr. Waldo.

02:16:24.644 --> 02:16:28.479
I know the man isn't responsible
for his actions,

02:16:28.481 --> 02:16:31.916
but in everything he's done
there's been a certain logic...

02:16:31.918 --> 02:16:37.487
and, you'll excuse me
for saying it, an integrity.

02:16:39.357 --> 02:16:43.459
I think he wants to...
be heard.

02:16:43.462 --> 02:16:46.564
That's all. I think that's
what he's wanted all along.

02:16:46.566 --> 02:16:50.700
If he blows himself up,
his story will die with him.

02:16:50.702 --> 02:16:54.939
I think he wants
to bring his case to court.

02:17:11.623 --> 02:17:14.959
- Library.
- <i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

02:17:16.827 --> 02:17:20.564
- Yes?
- Walker, I'll accept
your new conditions...

02:17:20.566 --> 02:17:24.968
if we can have a man
in there with you until
you give yourself up.

02:17:25.704 --> 02:17:27.737
All right then.
Send him over.

02:17:27.740 --> 02:17:30.406
Fine, fine.
Thank you, Mr. Walker.

02:17:30.409 --> 02:17:33.377
I'm looking forward
to meeting you.

02:17:34.745 --> 02:17:37.013
That's it.

02:17:37.482 --> 02:17:40.251
Keep your fingers crossed,
gentlemen.

02:17:40.253 --> 02:17:43.287
I'll believe it all
when it happens.

02:17:43.555 --> 02:17:48.791
Tell the militia to back off.
Keep them on standby.
Yes, sir.

02:17:48.927 --> 02:17:52.296
And get a new Model T
and check that it matches.

02:17:52.298 --> 02:17:53.897
Right.
Yes, sir.

02:17:53.898 --> 02:17:59.003
Good luck. Captain,
may I have a word with you?

02:17:59.004 --> 02:18:01.472
Yes, sir.

02:18:02.641 --> 02:18:08.445
Mr. Waldo, may I use the phone?
I want to call my family.

02:18:08.447 --> 02:18:10.714
Of course.

02:18:12.916 --> 02:18:16.287
What do you think?
That's okay.
[ Phone Ringing ]

02:18:16.289 --> 02:18:20.758
Essex and Sussex Hotel.
May I help you?

02:18:20.760 --> 02:18:24.295
Room 216 and 18.

02:18:26.698 --> 02:18:29.933
No, I'm sorry. They checked out
this morning, sir.

02:18:29.934 --> 02:18:32.770
Yes, sir. I'm quite sure.

02:18:32.772 --> 02:18:35.673
No. They didn't leave
any message.

02:18:35.674 --> 02:18:38.041
You're welcome.

02:18:42.347 --> 02:18:48.752
The area for two blocks
around J.P. Morgan's library...

02:18:48.754 --> 02:18:51.689
is now an emergency zone.

02:18:51.691 --> 02:18:55.925
Gentlemen,
the men you are following
must never suspect,

02:18:55.928 --> 02:18:59.697
repeat, <i>never</i> suspect, that
their car is under surveillance.

02:18:59.699 --> 02:19:05.968
<i>And no one makes a move</i>
<i>until you've got the full</i>
<i>go ahead from headquarters.</i>

02:19:06.971 --> 02:19:08.706
Understand?

02:19:08.708 --> 02:19:11.108
You shouldn't have any trouble
spotting the target car,

02:19:11.110 --> 02:19:17.348
unless there are a lot of new
Model Ts full of colored people
driving around all night.

02:19:17.350 --> 02:19:19.650
[ Laughter ]

02:19:20.518 --> 02:19:22.952
[ Whistle Blowing ]

02:19:35.933 --> 02:19:38.535
Coalhouse,
they're bringin' it! Look!

02:19:38.537 --> 02:19:40.971
[ Indistinct Chatter ]

02:20:31.089 --> 02:20:33.023
<i>[ Door Opens ]</i>

02:20:49.641 --> 02:20:51.842
Turn off all the lights.

02:21:09.727 --> 02:21:11.795
Take this.

02:21:11.797 --> 02:21:13.730
It's the telephone number here.

02:21:13.732 --> 02:21:17.901
The minute you're sure you're
safe and haven't been followed,
I want you to call me.

02:21:17.903 --> 02:21:20.103
- Wait a minute.
- I'm staying.

02:21:20.105 --> 02:21:21.638
<i>What?</i>
<i>What?</i>
<i>You heard me.</i>

02:21:21.640 --> 02:21:25.209
We ain't goin' nowhere
without you, brother.
We just can't do that.

02:21:25.211 --> 02:21:29.646
Think about it.
If I get out of here,

02:21:29.648 --> 02:21:33.250
I'd be hunted every day
of my life.

02:21:33.252 --> 02:21:36.687
And that's no kind of life
for a man.

02:21:36.689 --> 02:21:38.555
Is it?

02:21:38.557 --> 02:21:41.525
But no one's seen you.

02:21:42.026 --> 02:21:44.828
No one knows what you look like.

02:21:44.830 --> 02:21:47.097
Tomorrow you'll be free
in the streets.

02:21:47.099 --> 02:21:50.767
And you can start
gettin' folks to talkin'.

02:21:50.769 --> 02:21:54.571
Now that's got to be better
than five dead niggers.

02:21:54.573 --> 02:21:55.772
Coalhouse, you--

02:21:55.774 --> 02:22:01.178
Look! You all stay here,
and we're all dead men.

02:22:02.247 --> 02:22:05.015
Then what was all of this for?

02:22:06.918 --> 02:22:10.220
You all the only life
I got left.

02:22:10.222 --> 02:22:12.689
Now go on.

02:22:16.227 --> 02:22:19.096
Get on outta here!

02:22:26.204 --> 02:22:28.572
Go!

02:22:40.118 --> 02:22:42.686
[ Engine Idling ]

02:23:19.691 --> 02:23:22.159
How's my baby doin'?

02:23:23.061 --> 02:23:25.228
Fine.

02:23:26.698 --> 02:23:30.267
- He said any words yet?
- No.

02:23:31.235 --> 02:23:33.937
Oh, I--
I mean, I don't know.

02:23:33.939 --> 02:23:38.208
I... haven't heard him.

02:23:39.010 --> 02:23:44.114
If I was in prison,
I wonder if they'd let him come
and visit me.

02:23:44.116 --> 02:23:46.083
I don't see why not.

02:23:46.085 --> 02:23:51.855
<i>Um... you may find this</i>
<i>hard to believe right now,</i>

02:23:52.056 --> 02:23:54.057
but I believe--
I really do believe...

02:23:54.059 --> 02:23:58.095
that your situation,
legally speaking,

02:23:58.097 --> 02:24:02.399
isn't... at all hopeless.

02:24:04.402 --> 02:24:06.770
You think so?

02:24:06.772 --> 02:24:08.839
Mmm.

02:24:10.074 --> 02:24:13.076
You're an impressive
and articulate man.

02:24:13.078 --> 02:24:18.749
Certainly nothing like people
have been led to expect.

02:24:25.323 --> 02:24:27.991
I'd like to believe you.

02:24:29.360 --> 02:24:32.429
I really would like that.

02:24:34.032 --> 02:24:35.832
Mr. Walker,

02:24:35.834 --> 02:24:42.706
are you planning... to let me
leave this place alive?

02:24:46.711 --> 02:24:52.382
<i>[ Horse Carriage,</i>
<i>  Car Approaching ]</i>

02:25:03.695 --> 02:25:06.296
Sir? Sir, we lost them.

02:25:06.298 --> 02:25:09.066
Where?
We had them as far as 34th
and Lexington.

02:25:09.068 --> 02:25:13.403
They disappeared
before the next lookout post.
That's one block!

02:25:13.405 --> 02:25:17.741
Yes, sir.
Son of a b--

02:25:18.409 --> 02:25:21.278
[ Phone Ringing ]

02:25:25.016 --> 02:25:29.119
Y-You sure
you weren't followed?

02:25:29.121 --> 02:25:31.788
Good. Good.

02:25:31.790 --> 02:25:36.093
Don't worry about me.
I'll be fine.

02:25:37.729 --> 02:25:41.164
You all take care now,
you hear?

02:25:41.166 --> 02:25:43.433
All right.

02:25:54.011 --> 02:25:59.249
Are--
are they safe?

02:26:01.119 --> 02:26:03.253
Yeah.

02:26:14.932 --> 02:26:17.768
Well, shouldn't we...

02:26:17.770 --> 02:26:19.870
uh... tell them...

02:26:19.872 --> 02:26:23.106
that we're-- we're coming?

02:26:25.309 --> 02:26:27.511
Yeah.

02:26:30.481 --> 02:26:32.249
You go on ahead.

02:26:32.251 --> 02:26:35.152
Tell 'em  I'll be right out.

02:26:38.322 --> 02:26:42.125
- Well--
- Just go on. I'll be with you.

02:26:42.527 --> 02:26:44.060
- Don't--
- Go.

02:26:44.062 --> 02:26:48.999
[ Stammering ]
Don't you think it would be...

02:26:49.001 --> 02:26:50.934
a better idea if we--

02:26:50.936 --> 02:26:52.803
Get the hell out of here!

02:26:52.805 --> 02:26:56.473
Don't you understand anything,
white man?

02:26:56.841 --> 02:27:03.413
Oh, damn it! Damn it!
This is it! I know this is it!

02:27:13.558 --> 02:27:19.396
[ Walker ]
Lord, I'd hoped I'd have
the courage to know...

02:27:19.398 --> 02:27:21.565
what I should do now.

02:27:21.567 --> 02:27:25.902
You must see
how sick at heart I've been...

02:27:26.103 --> 02:27:31.174
and how I've performed
this thing with little appetite.

02:27:31.442 --> 02:27:35.912
I'd hoped... you'd reveal to me
along the way...

02:27:35.914 --> 02:27:40.150
why you put such a rage
in my heart.

02:27:45.189 --> 02:27:47.891
Tell me what to do now.

02:27:51.229 --> 02:27:52.629
Please.

02:27:52.631 --> 02:27:56.967
[ Sighs ]
God, tell me what to do.

02:28:25.630 --> 02:28:27.497
Fire.

02:28:27.499 --> 02:28:30.100
Sir?
Fire.

02:30:06.364 --> 02:30:09.466
[ Indistinct Chattering ]

02:30:13.137 --> 02:30:15.372
Champagne!

02:30:23.381 --> 02:30:25.615
Bye-bye!

02:30:37.695 --> 02:30:42.365
[ Boy ]
Extra! Extra! Read all about it!

02:30:46.270 --> 02:30:50.106
[ Cheering, Applauding ]

